      {
        "content": "Intensification is the GTA&rsquo;s new buzzword, and with good reason. But Richmond Hill&rsquo;s downtown, while intensifying, intends to retain its village-like character even though a few condominiums have quietly sprouted in the area, creating a work-in-progress skyline. According to Dave Barrow, mayor of Richmond Hill, the city grows two to three per cent annually, adding 3 to 4,000 new residents, which translates to about 1,000 units of new housing each year. But intensification cannot function without transit, he says. &lt;strong&gt;NO LAYOUT &ndash; IMAGE TEST:&lt;/strong&gt;",
        "_id": "1",
