      },
      {
        "content": "While many older residents are looking to downsize into condos, there&rsquo;s still demand from young families to remain in Richmond Hill and raise their children with adequate yard space. &ldquo;There is always going to be demand for single-family homes,&rdquo; said Heathwood&rsquo;s president, Hugh Heron. &ldquo;Places to Grow [the provincial intensification growth plan] is great to talk about, but you need balance too.&rdquo; Richmond Hill on the Green is very close to downtown, and given the latter&rsquo;s quaint village atmosphere, the city probably doesn&rsquo;t want to grow up too quickly like most municipalities in the immediate GTA are forced to. &lt;strong&gt;COLUMN &ndash; IMAGE TEST:&nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;",
        "_id": "11",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
