        "type": "wrapper",
        "shortcode": "[wrapper mobile=\"show\" desktop=\"show\" location=\"column\"]<img class=”wp-image-1095173 alignnone size-medium wp-image-1095173 alignnone size-medium” src=”http://new.nationalpost.wpdqa3.canada.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/19/2017/02/Tulips.jpg” alt=”” width=”300″ height=”225″ />[/wrapper]"
      },
      {
        "content": "Upton says the area has potential but it depends on town policies pertaining to land use. &ldquo;In their mind it&rsquo;s an historical strip of Yonge St. in their community, so naturally they want to maintain its heritage. There needs to be more development there, but it doesn&rsquo;t have to have significant density &mdash; just more character.&rdquo; &ldquo;Getting cars off the road is important to support the downtown core, which will have nice shops and nice cafes.&rdquo; In the heart of the Yonge St. downtown village is The Falcon Firkin, a local watering hole. &lt;strong&gt;SIDEBAR &ndash; IMAGE TEST:&lt;/strong&gt;",
        "_id": "13",
