      "main": "Encoding test"
    },
    "content_elements": [
      {
        "content": "The vote fit the opposition&rsquo;s theme of the week: that the government cares more about pleasing Bombardier bigwigs than listening to citizens outraged by the increases.",
        "_id": "1",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "&ldquo;We have a premier who has become the spokesman for Bombardier,&rdquo; Coalition Avenir Qu&eacute;bec Leader Fran&ccedil;ois Legault fired across the floor in question period. &ldquo;When will he become the spokesman for the people?&rdquo;",
        "_id": "2",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "But Premier Philippe Couillard said it was the Liberal party that stood up for Bombardier&rsquo;s workers with its $1.3 billion cash injection in 2016.",
        "_id": "3",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Legault opened a new front, saying Bombardier board chairman Pierre Beaudoin is earning much more than those&nbsp;in similar positions at&nbsp;other aircraft manufacturers.",
        "_id": "4",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "He said the chairman of Airbus in Europe earned 240,000 euros a year ($344,290) while Boeing&rsquo;s chair earns US$326,000 a year ($437,950). ",
        "_id": "5",
        "paragraph": "open",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "<a href=\"http://montrealgazette.com/news/quebec/we-goofed-on-boeing-chairmans-salary-caq\">The latter figure turned out to be a mistake, which the CAQ apologized for on Thursday</a>",
        "_id": "6",
        "type": "raw_html",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": ". Beaudoin earns $5 million Canadian a year even after his decision to pass on his wage increase.",
        "_id": "7",
        "paragraph": "close",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "&ldquo;I don&rsquo;t think it&rsquo;s up to the government to meddle in the internal affairs of a company unless it is a co-owner or (is)&nbsp;on the board, which is not the case,&rdquo; Couillard said, adding he, not the opposition, cares about the workers.",
        "_id": "8",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "&nbsp;",
        "_id": "9",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "&nbsp;",
        "_id": "10",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      }
