    "titles": {
      "main": "After popping the question, Ottawa man submits request to city for pond to be named after proposal"
    },
    "status": "published",
    "content_elements": [
      {
        "content": "An Ottawa man who asked his girlfriend to marry him&Acirc;&nbsp;one winter&acirc;s night during a skate on a south Ottawa pond&Acirc;&nbsp;wants the small body of water to be officially&Acirc;&nbsp;named &acirc;Proposal Pond.&acirc;",
        "_id": "1",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Greg Lister, a resident of Deerfield Village, proposed to his&Acirc;&nbsp;then-girlfriend Andrea last year by drawing&Acirc;&nbsp;the words of the proposal into the snow that covered the ice of the pond in Fawn Meadow Park, located on Meandering Brook Drive.",
        "_id": "2",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Ever since&Acirc;&nbsp;the couple&acirc;s&Acirc;&nbsp;engagement and subsequent wedding, the Lister family has apparently called the pond &acirc;proposal pond&acirc; and have &acirc;made new memories there with family and friends,&acirc; according to a commemorative naming proposal released by the city on Thursday.",
        "_id": "3",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Gloucester-Southgate Coun. Diane Deans, whose ward includes the park where the proposed &acirc;Proposal Pond&acirc; is located, said she submitted the request on behalf of Lister after he wrote her a letter outlining the couple&acirc;s romantic story.",
        "_id": "4",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "&acirc;It was meaningful to them and he asked if we would name the pond &acirc;Proposal Pond,&rsquo;&acirc; she said.&Acirc;&nbsp;&acirc;Anyone can propose a name for something&acirc;s that unnamed in the city.&acirc;",
        "_id": "5",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "<div id=\"fsk_splitbox_1715\" class=\" fsk_splitbox_1715\"></div>",
        "_id": "6",
        "type": "raw_html",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "The city&acirc;s commemorative naming committee is now conducting ",
        "_id": "7",
        "paragraph": "open",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "<a href=\"http://ottawa.ca/en/city-hall/your-city-government/policies-and-administrative-structure/current-commemorative-naming\"><span class=\"s1\">online public consultations</span></a>",
        "_id": "8",
        "type": "raw_html",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": " on this and seven other naming proposals. The deadline for submitting comments online is&Acirc;&nbsp;Dec. 18.",
        "_id": "9",
        "paragraph": "close",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Two other requests call for&Acirc;&nbsp;naming ice rinks in Kanata South in honour of Chris Neil and Chris Phillips.",
        "_id": "10",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Neil, who joined the Ottawa Senators in 2001, and his wife are co-chairs of Roger&acirc;s House, a hospice for pediatric palliative care, while&Acirc;&nbsp;Phillips, who retired at the end of last season, and&Acirc;&nbsp;his wife support several&Acirc;&nbsp;charities and not-for-profit organizations including the Children&acirc;s Hospital of Eastern Ontario, Candlelighters childhood cancer support program and Hockey Fights Cancer.",
        "_id": "11",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "<span lang=\"EN\" xml:lang=\"EN\">Commemorative naming of cityÂ streets, parks and facilities usually honours individuals who have demonstrated âexcellence, courage or exceptional serviceâ to the city, province or country; worked to foster equality and reduce discrimination or has a historical significance, according to the <a href=\"http://ottawa.ca/en/city-hall/your-city-government/policies-and-administrative-structure/commemorative-naming-policy\" target=\"_blank\">policy</a>.</span>",
        "_id": "12",
        "type": "raw_html",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Deans said her office is now&Acirc;&nbsp;conducting a survey among&Acirc;&nbsp;residents of&Acirc;&nbsp;the neighbourhood to see if they like the proposed name for the&Acirc;&nbsp;pond, which is currently nameless.",
        "_id": "13",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "&acirc;It&acirc;s a very sweet, sentimental story,&acirc; Deans said. &acirc;No one has proposed any other name for the pond, but I didn&acirc;t want to just accept it without giving the community an opportunity if they felt it should be named something else.&acirc;",
        "_id": "14",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Sweet as the story may be, however, the pond doesn&acirc;t just belong to the Lister family&Acirc;&nbsp;so why should they get to name it something that&acirc;s meaningful to them alone?",
        "_id": "15",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "They took the initiative, Deans said, adding: &acirc;They&acirc;re just proposing a name. It doesn&acirc;t mean that will be the name.",
        "_id": "16",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "&acirc;Who knows &acirc; maybe it will become a place where people go to propose, like the (Corktown) bridge with all the locks on it.&acirc;",
        "_id": "17",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Lister could not be reached for comment.",
        "_id": "18",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      }
    ],
