        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "It&acirc;s clear that Canadians drink far more wine these days than 10 or 20&Acirc;&nbsp;years ago. Wine has become part of lifestyle for many people, and the&Acirc;&nbsp;scores of web sites, books, blogs, newspaper columns, and apps reflect&Acirc;&nbsp;wide interest. Canadians now drink 15 litres of wine a head each year.&Acirc;&nbsp;That&acirc;s 20 bottles a year &acirc; about a bottle and a half a month &acirc; and it&acirc;s&Acirc;&nbsp;twice what we were drinking in 1990.",
        "_id": "3",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Americans drink less, 11 litres, but citizens of some countries drink&Acirc;&nbsp;much more. The French down 43 litres a year, the Italians 36 litres, and&Acirc;&nbsp;Germans 25 litres. Coming up quickly are Australians and New Zealanders,&Acirc;&nbsp;with 21 litres each. Some (like Canada) are increasing, but big consumers such as the French, Italians, and Spanish, having been&Acirc;&nbsp;drinking steadily less wine since the 1960s.",
        "_id": "4",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "The world&acirc;s biggest wine-drinkers? The people who live in the Vatican&Acirc;&nbsp;City top the table, with 50 litres each per year (just over a bottle a&Acirc;&nbsp;week). And people on small, isolated islands seem to find solace in wine&Acirc;&nbsp;bottles: St Helena, in the south Atlantic, and Norfolk Island, between Australia and New Zealand, are in the top five.",
        "_id": "5",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "The problem with per capita figures is that they include everyone:&Acirc;&nbsp;children, women and men. If you took out people under 15, you&acirc;d have a&Acirc;&nbsp;higher rate of wine consumption. And within the adult population, some&Acirc;&nbsp;groups drink more than others. Men drink more than women, poorer people&Acirc;&nbsp;drink less wine than the better-off, and older people drink more than&Acirc;&nbsp;younger people.",
        "_id": "6",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "<div id=\"fsk_splitbox_1715\" class=\" fsk_splitbox_1715\"></div>",
        "_id": "7",
        "type": "raw_html",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "This accounts to some extent for all the wine consumed in the Vatican&Acirc;&nbsp;City. They are nearly all adults, with a majority of men. I&acirc;m surprised&Acirc;&nbsp;their wine consumption isn&acirc;t higher. A bottle of wine a week isn&acirc;t even&Acirc;&nbsp;a small glass a day.",
        "_id": "8",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "In fact, &acirc;per capita consumption&acirc; is misleading: it&acirc;s really the amount&Acirc;&nbsp;of wine available to everyone. Consumption is much more restricted. For&Acirc;&nbsp;one thing, many adults never drink: about a third of Americans and a&Acirc;&nbsp;fifth of Italians and Canadians. Obviously, the more non-drinkers there&Acirc;&nbsp;are, the more wine is available to a smaller group of adults.",
        "_id": "9",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "How does your wine consumption fit into the picture? If you drink a&Acirc;&nbsp;bottle a week, you&acirc;re up there with the citizens of the Vatican. If you&Acirc;&nbsp;drink two bottles a week &acirc; a glass or two a day &acirc; you&acirc;re well up there&Acirc;&nbsp;and might find retiring to a remote island very congenial.",
        "_id": "10",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "<figure class=\"wp-caption post-img size_this_image_test aligncenter\" id=\"attachment_627462\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-627462\" src=\"http://wpmedia.ottawacitizen.com/2015/09/left-to-right-goats-do-roam-villa-maria-pinot-noir-guard.jpeg?quality=55&amp;strip=all\" alt=\"Goats do Roam, Villa Maria Pinot Noir, Guardian Red Blend, Ring Bolt Cabernet Sauvignon\"><figcaption class=\"wp-caption-text wp-caption\"><span class=\"img-caption\"> Goats Do Roam Red, Villa Maria Pinot Noir, Guardian Reserve Blend, Ringbolt Cabernet Sauvignon</span> <span class=\"img-author\"> Wayne Cuddington / Ottawa Citizen</span></figcaption></figure>",
        "_id": "11",
        "type": "raw_html",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "<h3>Goats do Roam Red 2014</h3>",
        "_id": "12",
        "type": "raw_html",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "From South Africa&acirc;s Western Cape region, this dry, shiraz-dominant blend&Acirc;&nbsp;delivers concentrated and nicely layered flavours right through, clean&Acirc;&nbsp;and fresh acidity, and light tannins. It goes well with barbecued red&Acirc;&nbsp;meats and sausages. 14-per cent alcohol; $12.95 (718940)",
        "_id": "13",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "<h3>Villa Maria Pinot Noir 2013</h3>",
        "_id": "14",
        "type": "raw_html",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "This is a quite richly flavoured pinot that&acirc;s very versatile with food.&Acirc;&nbsp;Try it with chicken, pork, and many red meats. The flavours are well&Acirc;&nbsp;defined with good complexity, and they&acirc;re supported by fresh acidity and&Acirc;&nbsp;framed by moderate tannins. 13.5-per cent alcohol; $19.95 (146548)",
        "_id": "15",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "<h3>Guardian Reserve Blend 2012</h3>",
        "_id": "16",
        "type": "raw_html",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Made from carmen&Atilde;&uml;re, cabernet sauvignon, merlot, and cabernet franc,&Acirc;&nbsp;this Chilean red is dry, fruity, and very approachable. The flavours are&Acirc;&nbsp;quite plush, the acidity is good, and the tannins easy-going. Drink it&Acirc;&nbsp;with burgers, ribs, and sausages. 14-per cent alcohol; $13.60 (392787)",
        "_id": "17",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "<h3>Ringbolt Cabernet Sauvignon 2013</h3>",
        "_id": "18",
        "type": "raw_html",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "This medium-full bodied cab from Margaret River in Western Australia&Acirc;&nbsp;delivers quality and value vintage after vintage. Look for solid,&Acirc;&nbsp;focused flavours, excellent fruit-acid balance, and ripe tannins. It&acirc;s&Acirc;&nbsp;for grilled red meats. 13.5-per cent alcohol; $21.95 (606624, Vintages",
        "_id": "19",
        "paragraph": "open",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "<br>",
        "_id": "20",
        "type": "raw_html",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": " Essential)",
        "_id": "21",
