      },
      {
        "content": "<strong>What:</strong>",
        "_id": "2",
        "type": "raw_html",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": " The Red Apron&acirc;s new Chili Dog.",
        "_id": "3",
        "paragraph": "close",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "<strong>Why:</strong>",
        "_id": "4",
        "type": "raw_html",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": " These are high-quality, fully&Acirc;&nbsp;loaded chili dogs, made with all-local ingredients. The all-beef hot dogs come from Enright Cattle Co., near Tweed, where the cattle are raised on a natural diet without artificial hormones. The delicious, hearty chili is made at the Red Apron, using&Acirc;&nbsp;beef from the Fitzroy Beef Farmers Co-operative, now based at the Two Rivers Food Hub in Smiths Falls. They&acirc;re nestled in&Acirc;&nbsp;house-made, poppyseed-sprinkled&Acirc;&nbsp;buns and topped with grated Cheddar from St-Albert Cheese Co-op.",
        "_id": "5",
        "paragraph": "close",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "&acirc;It&acirc;s been hard to get a good hot dog, and now we&acirc;ve got these from Enright, we wanted to make something special,&acirc; says Red Apron owner Jennifer Heagle. &acirc;Fall, and&Acirc;&nbsp;baseball season, seem like&Acirc;&nbsp;a good time for a chili dog.&acirc;",
        "_id": "6",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "<strong>What else:</strong>",
        "_id": "7",
        "type": "raw_html",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": " You can buy packages of four frozen Enright all-beef hot dogs for $6.95 at the Red Apron.",
        "_id": "8",
        "paragraph": "close",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
