      {
        "content": "<ol>\n<li>Cook sprouts in a large pot of boiling salted water 10 seconds. Transfer to a clean kitchen towel with a slotted spoon; let cool. Cooking in separate batches, repeat with snow peas, carrots, and cabbage (do cabbage last and keep it separate while cooling so it doesnât colour the other vegetables). Pat dry if needed.</li> <li>Pulse chiles, garlic, ginger, brown sugar, and 1 tspÂ (5 mL)Â salt in a food processor until very finely chopped. Transfer pureÌe to a large bowl; add lime leaves, coconut, sprouts, peas, and carrots and toss to combine. Season with salt if needed.</li> <li>â©Toss in cabbage just before serving.</li> </ol>",
