    "origin_url": "http://ottawacitizen.wpdev5.canada.com/entertainment/books/class-action-accuses-one-of-canadas-biggest-nursing-home-companies-of-neglecting-residents/wcm/15930aa6-2c23-48da-8256-e46ea0c1ddad",
    "status": "published",
    "titles": {
      "main": "Class action accuses one of Canada’s biggest nursing-home companies of neglecting residents"
    },
    "content_elements": [
      {
        "content": "A Toronto malpractice lawyer is launching what she calls an unprecedented class-action lawsuit against one of Canada&acirc;s biggest nursing-home companies, charging that it routinely neglects or mistreats elderly residents.",
        "_id": "1",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "The multimillion-dollar suit was prompted by the case of Ross Jones, a 68-year-old man who allegedly spent the last days of his life in agony, an infected pressure sore left untreated by a Revera Inc. facility.",
        "_id": "2",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "But the case &acirc; to be officially unveiled at a news conference Thursday &acirc; underscores persistent complaints throughout the country that some long-term care homes deliver substandard care.",
        "_id": "3",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Revera counters that it is &acirc;very proud&acirc; of its service, noting that it looks after people near the end of their lives and frequently suffering from a complex array of ailments.",
        "_id": "4",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Lawyer Amani Oakley said she often hears from relatives about cases like Jones&acirc; but the economics of suing a nursing home are prohibitive, the damages awarded for an elderly patient dwarfed by the costs of litigation.",
        "_id": "5",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "<div id=\"fsk_splitbox_1715\" class=\"  fsk_splitbox_1715\"></div>",
        "_id": "6",
        "type": "raw_html",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "A class action involving a number of plaintiffs potentially changes those dynamics, making it feasible to pursue a lengthy civil suit even if any compensation awarded to individuals is limited, Oakley said in an interview Wednesday.",
        "_id": "7",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "&acirc;We need the giant and very profitable Revera conglomerate to hear the message loud and clear that Mr. Jones&acirc; suffering and death and the negative and unacceptable experiences of other residents is unacceptable,&acirc; she said in a statement.",
        "_id": "8",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Though it is a private business, Mississauga, Ont.-based Revera is wholly owned by the Public Sector Pension Investment Board, a federal Crown corporation. Revera, whose board &acirc;chair emeritus&acirc; is former Ontario premier Bill Davis, owns or operates 500 facilities in Canada, the U.S. and the U.K.",
        "_id": "9",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "John Beaney, a Revera vice-president, said Wednesday he could not comment on the specifics of the allegations, but argued the suit lacks merit.",
        "_id": "10",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "&acirc;We&acirc;ve been operating as an organization for more than 50 years &acirc;&brvbar; and have successfully cared for hundreds of thousands of people,&acirc; he said. &Acirc;&nbsp;&acirc;We&acirc;re very proud of our dedicated employees who provide that care.&acirc;",
        "_id": "11",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "He also noted that nursing home residents have increasingly complex health issues, their deaths often a result of multiple factors.",
        "_id": "12",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "&acirc;When a resident passes away &acirc;&brvbar; it&acirc;s not black and white and this can understandably make it difficult for loved ones, who seek answers in those cases.&acirc;",
        "_id": "13",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "The class action&acirc;s first plaintiffs are Lori DeKervor and her late father, Ross Jones, who died in June 2014.",
        "_id": "14",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Diagnosed with Parkinson&acirc;s disease and dementia, he had been a resident at Main Street Terrace, a Revera home in Toronto.",
        "_id": "15",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "The suit alleges that Jones was rushed to hospital late that May, unable to speak, with an elevated heart rate and temperature. Days later, noticing her father was in pain whenever he was moved, DeKervor discovered he had a &acirc;large, deep, smelly, oozing sacral ulcer&acirc; at the base of his spine &acirc; a bed sore that had become infected.",
        "_id": "16",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "title": "Image title",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ],
        "_id": "17",
        "url": "http://wpmedia.ottawacitizen.com/2016/10/mayor-jim-watson-with-his-sister-jayne-watson-and-ottawa-sy.jpeg?w=140crop=1",
        "type": "image"
      },
      {
        "content": "It&acirc;s alleged the nursing home did not take proper measures to prevent the wound.",
        "_id": "18",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "&acirc;There has to be some way to get justice for my Dad,&acirc; the daughter said in a statement issued by Oakley. &acirc;He deserved better than this. He died a painful, 13th-century death, while being looked after by a giant business entity that is making a ton of money.&acirc;",
        "_id": "19",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "The home has been inspected by Ontario&acirc;s health and long-term care ministry 16 times since the beginning of 2014, mostly because of complaints or &acirc;critical incidents.&acirc;",
        "_id": "20",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "The most recent review, last month, seems reminiscent of Jones&acirc; case. It resulted in two &acirc;written notifications&acirc; of rule infractions, involving a resident who had allegedly not been repositioned every two hours as required because of sores.",
        "_id": "21",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Once Revera has filed a statement of defence, a judge must decide whether to &acirc;certify&acirc; the class-action lawsuit, allowing it to move ahead to settlement or trial.",
        "_id": "22",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      }
