          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "<a href=\"http://ottawacitizen.com/tag/canadian-human-rights-commission\" target=\"_blank\">Canadian Human Rights Commission</a>",
        "_id": "4",
        "type": "raw_html",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": " to restart its investigation into a discrimination complaint from a public servant diagnosed with Asperger&acirc;s syndrome.",
        "_id": "5",
        "paragraph": "close",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Robert Dupuis, who has worked at ",
        "_id": "6",
        "paragraph": "open",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "<a href=\"http://ottawacitizen.com/tag/statistics-canada\" target=\"_blank\">Statistics Canada</a>",
        "_id": "7",
        "type": "raw_html",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": " since 1990, filed the complaint with the commission in 2011, alleging that his employer had discriminated against him on the basis of his disability.",
        "_id": "8",
        "paragraph": "close",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "The commission spent 15 months investigating the complaint before dismissing it in October 2015.",
        "_id": "9",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Its decision noted that Statistics Canada had implemented accommodation measures recommended by Health Canada and had tried to accommodate Dupuis for several years before demoting him.",
        "_id": "10",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "The commission also found that Statistics Canada had made a reasonable offer of settlement to Dupuis during a failed attempt at conciliation.",
        "_id": "11",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "<div id=\"fsk_splitbox_1715\" class=\" fsk_splitbox_1715\"></div>",
        "_id": "12",
        "type": "raw_html",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Dupuis sought judicial review by the Federal Court of the commission&acirc;s decision to dismiss his complaint, alleging that it had treated him unfairly in the investigation process.",
        "_id": "13",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "He also argued that the commission erred in concluding he had been reasonably accommodated by his employer and that&Acirc;&nbsp;it should not have relied on the settlement offer, which he alleged&Acirc;&nbsp;was not reasonable, in its reasons for dismissing his complaint.",
        "_id": "14",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Dupuis was diagnosed in 2004 with Asperger&acirc;s syndrome,&Acirc;&nbsp;a developmental disorder",
        "_id": "15",
        "paragraph": "open",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "<b>Â </b>",
        "_id": "16",
        "type": "raw_html",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "characterized by difficulties in social interaction and non-verbal communication as well as&Acirc;&nbsp;restricted and repetitive patterns of behaviour and interests.",
        "_id": "17",
        "paragraph": "close",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Following his diagnosis, Health Canada recommended three accommodation measures that could improve his job performance.",
        "_id": "18",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "In a 2005 followup report, Health Canada made four additional suggestions for accommodating him, including getting&Acirc;&nbsp;a consultant&Acirc;&nbsp;to come into the workplace to help him.",
        "_id": "19",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "While Statistics Canada acted on most of the recommendations, it never hired an expert to assist it in accommodating Dupuis while he was&Acirc;&nbsp;a subject matter/information technology officer, a job classified at the S1-03 level.",
        "_id": "20",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Despite the accommodation measures, Dupuis received a succession of unsatisfactory performance reviews and was gradually assigned reduced responsibilities. He was demoted to a clerical position in 2008.",
        "_id": "21",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "However, he didn&acirc;t report for work in his new position and instead went on a medically approved stress leave until 2012.",
        "_id": "22",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "While still on leave, he filed his complaint with the human rights commission, claiming that Statistics Canada had discriminated against him on the basis of his disability and had failed to properly accommodate him.",
        "_id": "23",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "In her&Acirc;&nbsp;",
        "_id": "24",
        "paragraph": "open",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "<a href=\"http://www.canlii.org/en/ca/fct/doc/2016/2016fc1137/2016fc1137.html\" target=\"_blank\">decision</a>",
        "_id": "25",
        "type": "raw_html",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": ",&Acirc;&nbsp;Judge Anne Mactavish, a former chair of the Canadian Human Rights Tribunal, noted the sufficiency of Statistics Canada&acirc;s efforts to accommodate Dupuis was &acirc;front and centre&acirc; in his human rights complaint.",
        "_id": "26",
        "paragraph": "close",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "However, the human rights commission&acirc;s investigator never addressed the agency&acirc;s failure to hire a consultant to assist in accommodating Dupuis in his S1-03 position, she said.",
        "_id": "27",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "&acirc;Rather, the investigator simply concluded that Statistics Canada had done everything that it could to try to accommodate Mr. Dupuis&acirc; disability, without success, leaving it with no alternative but to demote him to a clerical position, three levels below his SI-03 position,&acirc; her decision says.",
        "_id": "28",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "&acirc;The failure of the investigator to engage with this key evidence means that&Acirc;&nbsp;the commission decision lacks the justification, transparency and intelligibility required of a reasonable decision,&acirc; Mactavish concluded.",
        "_id": "29",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Moreover, the commission&acirc;s assessment of the reasonableness of Statistics Canada&acirc;s settlement offer to Dupuis was based on the investigator&acirc;s finding that it had fully implemented the accommodation measures recommended by Health Canada, she continued.",
        "_id": "30",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "But the fact that the investigator never considered Statistics Canada&acirc;s failure to hire a consultant &acirc;undermines the reasonableness&acirc; of the finding that it had fully discharged its duty to accommodate Dupuis, Mactavish said.",
        "_id": "31",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "That, in turn, calls into question the reasonableness of its assessment of the agency&acirc;s offer of settlement, she said.",
        "_id": "32",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Mactavish ordered the commission to set aside its decision dismissing Dupuis&acirc; human rights complaint and sent it back for further investigation.",
        "_id": "33",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "<a href=\"mailto:dbutler@postmedia.com\">dbutler@postmedia.com</a>",
        "_id": "34",
        "type": "raw_html",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "<a href=\"http://twitter.com/ButlerDon\" target=\"_blank\">twitter.com/ButlerDon</a>",
        "_id": "35",
        "type": "raw_html",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "<strong>The evolution of Aspergerâs</strong>",
        "_id": "36",
        "type": "raw_html",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Asperger syndrome is one of several previously separate subtypes of autism that were folded into the single diagnosis of autism spectrum disorder (ASD) in 2013.",
        "_id": "37",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Asperger syndrome was generally considered to be on the &acirc;high functioning&acirc; end of the spectrum. Those affected have difficulty with social interactions and exhibit a restricted range of interests or repetitive behaviours. Motor development may be delayed, leading to clumsiness or uncoordinated motor movements. Compared with those affected by other forms of ASD, those with Asperger syndrome do not have significant delays or difficulties in language or cognitive development. Some even demonstrate precocious vocabulary, often in a highly specialized field of interest.",
        "_id": "38",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      }
    ],
