        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "<span style=\"font-size: 11px\">-9.</span>",
        "_id": "13",
        "type": "raw_html",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Last season, the Senators beat the Jets in two of their three games, outscoring them by an aggregate score of eight to three. Ottawa&acirc;s power play clicked on three of its ten opportunities and its goaltenders stopped 88 of 91 shots to the tune of a .967 save percentage.",
        "_id": "14",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "In Ottawa&acirc;s one loss to the Jets on February 9, 2013, Al Montoya stopped 33 shots to preserve a 1-0 shutout.",
        "_id": "15",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "<strong>Storylines…</strong>",
        "_id": "16",
        "type": "raw_html",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "After yesterday&acirc;s announcement by USA Hockey that Blake Wheeler had made their Olympic team at the expense of Senators forward Bobby Ryan, Senators fans will get their first glimpse of a scorned and motivated Ryan.",
        "_id": "17",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Tonight&acirc;s goaltending matchup will culminate with one goaltender&acirc;s winning streak coming to an end.",
        "_id": "18",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Having won three consecutive starts for the second time this season, Craig Anderson will get the start in goal for Ottawa. In his last five games versus Winnipeg, Anderson has a 4-1-0 record, a 2.41 goals against average and a save percentage of .937.",
        "_id": "19",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "The Jets have also won three consecutive games thanks in large part to their announced starter for tonight&acirc;s game, Al Montoya. Montoya is coming off a 27-save shutout performance versus Buffalo and he has also won his last six starts.",
        "_id": "20",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "In fact, Montoya has posted some impressive peripherals this season. His 1.85 goals against average and his .934 save percentage have allowed him to a compile an 8-2-1 record.",
        "_id": "21",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "His performance of late is welcomed change because Winnipeg&acirc;s regular starter, Ondrej Pavelec, has only won once in his last nine starts.",
        "_id": "22",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Chris Phillips will also make his return to the lineup after sustaining a foot injury while blocking a shot in Friday night&acirc;s game in Boston. Chris Neil and Jason Spezza will remain out of the lineup for the Senators.",
        "_id": "23",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Jim Slater, Grant Clitsome, Paul Postma and Matt Halischuk will be out of the lineup for the Jets.",
        "_id": "24",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "<strong>Interesting Stat #1</strong>",
        "_id": "25",
        "type": "raw_html",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Since being snubbed, many have emphasized the importance of Bobby Ryan being able to remain in Ottawa and rest during the Olympic break. Obviously there is a larger time difference between this year&acirc;s Olympic Games in Sochi and the 2010 Games in Vancouver, but in looking back at Ryan&acirc;s performance during the 2009/10 season before and after the Olympics, there was not much of a difference.",
        "_id": "26",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "<table border=\"1\" width=\"509\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\"><tbody>\n<tr>\n<td valign=\"top\" width=\"98\"> <p align=\"center\"><strong>2009/10 Season</strong></p> </td> <td valign=\"top\" width=\"106\"> <p align=\"center\"><strong>Games Played</strong></p> </td> <td valign=\"top\" width=\"37\"> <p align=\"center\"><strong>G</strong></p> </td> <td valign=\"top\" width=\"40\"> <p align=\"center\"><strong>Pts</strong></p> </td> <td valign=\"top\" width=\"55\"> <p align=\"center\"><strong>Shots</strong></p> </td> <td valign=\"top\" width=\"81\"> <p align=\"center\"><strong>Pts/Game</strong></p> </td> <td valign=\"top\" width=\"93\"> <p align=\"center\"><strong>Shots/Game</strong></p> </td> </tr>\n<tr>\n<td valign=\"top\" width=\"98\"> <p align=\"center\"><strong>Before Olympics</strong></p> </td> <td valign=\"top\" width=\"106\"> <p align=\"center\">62</p> </td> <td valign=\"top\" width=\"37\"> <p align=\"center\">28</p> </td> <td valign=\"top\" width=\"40\"> <p align=\"center\">49</p> </td> <td valign=\"top\" width=\"55\"> <p align=\"center\">192</p> </td> <td valign=\"top\" width=\"81\"> <p align=\"center\">0.79</p> </td> <td valign=\"top\" width=\"93\"> <p align=\"center\">3.09</p> </td> </tr>\n<tr>\n<td valign=\"top\" width=\"98\"> <p align=\"center\"><strong>After Olympics</strong></p> </td> <td valign=\"top\" width=\"106\"> <p align=\"center\">19</p> </td> <td valign=\"top\" width=\"37\"> <p align=\"center\">7</p> </td> <td valign=\"top\" width=\"40\"> <p align=\"center\">15</p> </td> <td valign=\"top\" width=\"55\"> <p align=\"center\">66</p> </td> <td valign=\"top\" width=\"81\"> <p align=\"center\">0.78</p> </td> <td valign=\"top\" width=\"93\"> <p align=\"center\">3.43</p> </td> </tr>\n</tbody></table>\n",
        "_id": "27",
        "type": "raw_html",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "<strong>Interesting Stat #2</strong>",
        "_id": "28",
        "type": "raw_html",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Ottawa has only lost twice on home ice to the Jets since the team moved from Atlanta to Winnipeg. Interestingly, in each of these losses, the Senators were shut out.",
        "_id": "29",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "<strong>Interesting Stat #3</strong>",
        "_id": "30",
        "type": "raw_html",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "After boasting the league&acirc;s best penalty kill success rate during the 2012-13 season, the Senators have not gone three consecutive games without allowing a power play goal.",
        "_id": "31",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "The team has gone two games without allowing a power play goal on three separate occasions this season, including its latest games against the Bruins and Capitals, but will be looking to extend their current streak to three tonight.",
        "_id": "32",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Last season, there were only two games in which the Senators allowed more than one power play goal in a game. This season, the feat has happened eight times.",
        "_id": "33",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "<strong>Interesting Stat #4</strong>",
        "_id": "34",
        "type": "raw_html",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "With an 11-3-0 record versus Eastern Conference opponents, the Jets probably wish they were still playing in the East against weaker competition.",
        "_id": "35",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "<strong>Interesting Stat #5</strong>",
        "_id": "36",
        "type": "raw_html",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "According to ",
        "_id": "37",
        "paragraph": "open",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "<a href=\"http://www.extraskater.com/players/on-ice?dir=reverse&amp;sort=ga\">ExtraSkater.com</a>",
        "_id": "38",
        "type": "raw_html",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": ", no player has been on the ice for more goals allowed this season than Dustin Byfuglien with 44.",
        "_id": "39",
        "paragraph": "close",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "If Byfuglien&rsquo;s plus/minus rating played a big a part in being removed from the United States&rsquo; Olympic team consideration, he can thank his goaltenders for contributing to his omission by recording an .887 save percentage while he is on the ice.",
        "_id": "40",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "<strong>Â Interesting Stat #6</strong>",
        "_id": "41",
        "type": "raw_html",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "There&rsquo;s a 100-percent probability that Bobby Ryan ",
        "_id": "42",
        "paragraph": "open",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "<a href=\"http://espn.go.com/olympics/hockey/story/_/id/10195703/how-us-hockey-team-bound-sochi-olympics-was-named\">can spell intense</a>",
        "_id": "43",
        "type": "raw_html",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": ".",
        "_id": "44",
