    "origin_url": "http://ottawacitizen.wpdev5.canada.com/business/local-business/cats-and-dogs-coming-rainfall-warning-issued/wcm/8b0593df-f8f3-4b23-9187-ac2eba11ba26",
    "status": "published",
    "titles": {
      "main": "Cats and dogs coming: Rainfall warning issued"
    },
    "content_elements": [
      {
        "height": 497,
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ],
        "type": "image",
        "width": 662,
        "title": "Image title",
        "_id": "1",
        "url": "http://wpmedia.ottawacitizen.com/2015/05/116906-pedestrians-on-bank-st-armed-with-umbrellas-to-shelte.jpg?quality=55&strip=all&w=840&h=630&crop=1"
      },
      {
        "content": "&nbsp;",
        "_id": "2",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "A rainfall warning is in effect for the Ottawa region, with 40 to 60 mm of rain expected to fall on the area over the next 24 hours.",
        "_id": "3",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "According to Environment Canada, the deluge is expected to begin late Tuesday morning or early afternoon, and continue overnight and possibly into Wednesday morning. Thunderstorms are also expected.",
        "_id": "4",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "The high Tuesday is predicted to be 24 C, with a humidex of 30. The low will drop to 18 C.",
        "_id": "5",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "A &acirc;moisture-laden disturbance from Texas&acirc; is being blamed for the expected downpour. Flash floods are a possibility, as is water pooling on roads and localized flooding in low-lying areas.",
        "_id": "6",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      }
    ],
