    "origin_url": "http://ottawacitizen.wpdev5.canada.com/business/local-business/new-duke-of-westminster-a-25-year-old-who-inherited-13-9b-has-ties-in-vancouver/wcm/bdc6529a-7231-41a3-b044-6f36c4190109",
    "status": "published",
    "titles": {
      "main": "New Duke of Westminster, a 25-year-old who inherited $13.9B, has ties in Vancouver"
    },
    "content_elements": [
      {
        "title": "Image title",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ],
        "_id": "1",
        "url": "http://www.ottawacitizen.com/news/national/cms/binary/12122305.jpg?size=640x420",
        "type": "image"
      },
      {
        "content": "A 25-year-old man just became one of the most eligible bachelors in the world &acirc;&Acirc;&nbsp;and he has ties to Vancouver.",
        "_id": "2",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "It is not something he would have wished for himself, but at the age of 25 Hugh Richard Louis Grosvenor has been left contemplating the fact that overnight he has become Britain&acirc;s most eligible bachelor.",
        "_id": "3",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Following the sudden death of the Duke of Westminster at the age of 64 on Tuesday, the young account manager has inherited his father&acirc;s title and estate, making him one of the richest men in the world.",
        "_id": "4",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Until now the new Duke had lived a life of relative obscurity for someone so gilded &acirc; save for a memorable 21st birthday party rumoured to have cost several million. But his sudden elevation will put him in the spotlight as never before, raising the question: Just who is the seventh Duke of Westminster?",
        "_id": "5",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "By inheriting the bulk of his father&acirc;s fortune, estimated at CAD$13.9 billion by Forbes, the new Duke becomes the third richest person in the U.K. and the 68th wealthiest in the world. At the heart of the family fortune is a property portfolio which includes 300 acres in two of London&acirc;s most expensive neighbourhoods, Mayfair and Belgravia, as well as huge tracts in Oxford, Cheshire, Scotland and Spain.",
        "_id": "6",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "<div id=\"fsk_splitbox_1715\" class=\" fsk_splitbox_1715\"></div>",
        "_id": "7",
        "type": "raw_html",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "What many may not know is that the family&acirc;s wealth, first started more than 400 years ago, includes Grosvenor Group, a real estate arm with significant holdings in Metro Vancouver, including the mighty Annacis Island.",
        "_id": "8",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "<strong>Annacis Island, Grosvenorâs first international foray</strong>",
        "_id": "9",
        "type": "raw_html",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Annacis Island may be a secret short cut for traffic-weary commuters trying to get onto the Alex Fraser Bridge, as well as being the home of Metro Vancouver&acirc;s main sewage treatment plant, but it had nobler beginnings, at least for Grosvenor. The family trust bought the 1,200-acre island in 1953 as its first international project. Annacis, once a former farming and fishing island in the middle of the Fraser River, became Canada&acirc;s first industrial park. The island is now fully developed as an industrial hub, but Grosvenor still owns 210 acres and nine industrial buildings covering 1.1 million square feet.",
        "_id": "10",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "<strong>Grosvenorâs Metro Vancouver holdings and projects</strong>",
        "_id": "11",
        "type": "raw_html",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Since Annacis, Grosvenor has diversified into residential and commercial property development. The company has a long list of completed projects in B.C., and has four active ones: the 57-unit Grosvenor Ambleside in West Vancouver; the 82-unit Connaught; the 212-unit Grosvenor Pacific at 1380-1382 Hornby St., including a heritage restoration of the 1888 Leslie House, once the home of Umberto Menghi&acirc;s Il Giardino restaurant; and a 60-townhome project on Oak Street between 46th and 49th Avenues. Last November, Grosvenor also announced a $165-million financing partnership with Vancouver-based Kingswood Capital and Nicola Wealth Management to provide mezzanine financing for 10 condo projects in B.C. and the U.S., including Intracorp&acirc;s Belpark in Vancouver, Boffo Development&acirc;s Pitt River Development, and Millennium Development&acirc;s Gilmore project in Burnaby. &acirc;This is the largest pipeline of projects we&acirc;ve had in the last 30 years,&acirc; said Michael Ward, Grosvenor&acirc;s senior vice-president and general manager of the Vancouver office.",
        "_id": "12",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "<strong>Royal real estate</strong>",
        "_id": "13",
        "type": "raw_html",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Grosvenor&acirc;s North American real estate properties are distinctly pedestrian compared to the origins and addresses of its original holdings. The family&acirc;s history reaches back nearly a millennium to William the Conqueror, and its wealth flows from the 1677 marriage of Mary Davies and Sir Thomas Grosvenor, which gave the family title to 500 acres of what would become central London. It still owns 300 acres there, including 190 acres in Belgravia, adjacent to Buckingham Palace, the land for which was also provided by the Grosvenors. They also retain their ancestral home, the 10,800-acre Eaton Hall estate. When the Duke died on Tuesday, he was the 68th-wealthiest person in the world and the third-richest in the U.K.",
        "_id": "14",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "<strong>The Duke and the Lightshed</strong>",
        "_id": "15",
        "type": "raw_html",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "People strolling along the seawall in Vancouver&acirc;s Harbour Green Park at Coal Harbour can stop and admire a peculiarly West Coast piece of public art, what looks like a silver boat shed on pilings. Liz Magor&acirc;s &acirc;Lightshed&acirc; was commissioned and dedicated by the now-departed Duke in 2003 to commemorate Grosvenor&acirc;s half-century of business in Canada. The family also has an elementary school and road in Surrey named after them. &acirc;We take a very long-term view of business, and Vancouver historically has given us our highest return in the Americas,&acirc; Gerald Grosvenor told The Province&acirc;s Ashley Ford after the dedication. Grosvenor Group would not say whether the new Duke has ever been to Vancouver.",
        "_id": "16",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "<strong>What we know about the new Duke</strong>",
        "_id": "17",
        "type": "raw_html",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "In a few words, not much. Hugh Grosvenor may now be the most eligible bachelor in the U.K., but he apparently has a somewhat humble childhood and is understandably private. He attended a public school, then Newcastle university and works for bio-bean, a London-based green technology company that recycles coffee grounds into biofuels. His one bit of unwanted public attention was a massive 5-million pound ($8.4-million) party his father hosted for him at Eaton Hall for his 21st birthday. His father made it clear early on that he might be extraordinarily wealthy some day, but that he had to earn his place in life. In 1993, when his son was two, the Duke said in an interview that, &acirc;He&acirc;s been born with the longest silver spoon anyone can have, but he can&acirc;t go through life sucking on it. He has to put back what he has been given.&acirc;",
        "_id": "18",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      }
    ],
