    "origin_url": "http://ottawacitizen.wpdev5.canada.com/entertainment/books/harry-potter-and-the-cursed-child-sells-an-unprecedented-two-million-copies-in-two-days-in-u-s-and-canada/wcm/16b3d90c-4307-4542-8765-d04a85a41c22",
    "status": "published",
    "titles": {
      "main": "Harry Potter and the Cursed Child sells an ‘unprecedented’ two million copies in two days in U.S. and Canada"
    },
    "content_elements": [
      {
        "title": "Image title",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ],
        "_id": "1",
        "url": "http://www.ottawacitizen.com/entertainment/cms/binary/12101047.jpg?size=sw620x65",
        "type": "image"
      },
      {
        "content": "&nbsp;",
        "_id": "2",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "According to Scholastic, the script book for Harry Potter and the Cursed Child has already sold over two million copies in the U.S. and Canada in its first two days in bookstores. In the U.K.,&Acirc;&nbsp;over&Acirc;&nbsp;680,000 copies were sold in just three days, becoming the fastest selling book since the last Potter novel, reports ",
        "_id": "3",
        "paragraph": "open",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "<a href=\"http://www.ew.com/article/2016/08/03/harry-potter-cursed-child-two-day-sales\" target=\"_blank\">Entertainment Weekly</a>",
        "_id": "4",
        "type": "raw_html",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": ".",
        "_id": "5",
        "paragraph": "close",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Scholastic has called the early sales&Acirc;&nbsp;&acirc;unprecedented for a script book,&acirc; according to The Guardian.",
        "_id": "6",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "For fans of the series, the early sales are not entirely surprising, as many flocked in full Hogwarts garb&Acirc;&nbsp;to midnight parties and late night lineups outside bookstores in preparation for the release of the popular series&acirc; latest instalment &acirc; just like they did years before, for the original novels.",
        "_id": "7",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "However, Cursed Child is more of an adaptation of the series, having been brought to the London stage this summer. Author J.K. Rowling has been adamant that the story is not a sequel, though it is set 19 years after the last novel, Harry Potter and the Deathly Hallows.",
        "_id": "8",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Based on a story by Rowling and John Tiffany, the script itself was penned by Jack Thorne. The original seven novels, all written by Rowling, sold over 450 million copies worldwide.",
        "_id": "9",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      }
    ],
