    "titles": {
      "main": "Netflix announces 'Gilmore Girls,' 'One Day At A Time' dates"
    },
    "content_elements": [
      {
        "content": "NEW YORK, N.Y. &ndash; The television revivals at Netflix that began in February with &ldquo;Fuller House&rdquo; continue as the streaming network announces premiere dates for two more series reboots.",
        "_id": "1",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Netflix says &ldquo;Gilmore Girls: A Year in the Life&rdquo; will debut globally on Nov. 25. A new Latino version of &ldquo;One Day at a Time&rdquo; premieres Jan. 6.",
        "_id": "2",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "The new &ldquo;Gilmore Girls&rdquo; brings back the popular mother-daughter dramedy that aired from 2000 to 2007. Each of the four 90-minute chapters covers each of four seasons of the year. The series brings back original stars Lauren Graham and Alexis Bledel, with creator Amy Sherman-Palladino also returning.",
        "_id": "3",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "The new &ldquo;One Day a Time&rdquo; reimagines the 1970s sitcom classic, this time centring on a Cuban-American family. Original producer Norman Lear is back for its 13-episode first season.",
        "_id": "4",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      }
    ],
