      {
        "content": "Environment Canada is warning residents of the nation&acirc;s capital of an incoming storm that could bring as much as 60 millimetres of rain on Tuesday afternoon.",
        "_id": "4",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "According to the federal weather agency, clouds are expected to roll in on Tuesday morning with rain expected to start falling in the late afternoon. The high for the day will be 24 C, with a humidex of 30. The rain, which will bring between 25 mm and 44 mm of rainfall to most areas, is expected to end late Tuesday night or Wednesday morning.",
        "_id": "5",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Monday is expected to be a mix of sun and cloud along with a high of 27 C with a humidex of 32.",
