    "origin_url": "http://ottawacitizen.wpdev5.canada.com/news/local-news/just-a-regular-lowly-construction-worker/wcm/64491eb0-1a45-4dd6-8a99-a695e24a2fc7",
    "status": "published",
    "titles": {
      "main": "Regular construction worker"
    },
    "content_elements": [
      {
        "content": "Police are mobilizing every resource to investigate four shootings that happened on Sunday, including the night-club killing of a known gang member&Acirc;&nbsp;in which&Acirc;&nbsp;an armed suspect is still at large, brass told a hastily-arranged press conference Monday.",
        "_id": "1",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Potential links between the incidents of gunplay are being investigated and police are asking anyone with information to come forward &acirc; while promising to protect them from any retaliation &acirc; and reassuring all Ottawans that the city remains safe.",
        "_id": "2",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "But in three decades of policing, Supt. Don Sweet said he doesn&acirc;t think he&acirc;s ever seen four shootings in the span of 12 or 13 hours.",
        "_id": "3",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Police rallied officers from forensics, guns and gangs, general investigations and patrol over multiple scenes with lots of evidence and witnesses, Sweet said.",
        "_id": "4",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "He said he&acirc;s confident there will be an arrest soon in the homicide of Omar Rashid-Ghader, 33, who was shot multiple times inside Sentral Night Club in the Byward Market at about 3:20 a.m. Sunday.",
        "_id": "5",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "<div id=\"fsk_splitbox_1715\" class=\" fsk_splitbox_1715\"></div>",
        "_id": "6",
        "type": "raw_html",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "A known association of the dead man, 28-year-old Mustafa Ahmed, is wanted for second-degree murder.",
        "_id": "7",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "&acirc;He is considered armed and dangerous,&acirc; Sweet said. &acirc;Somebody knows where this person is. We have to get him off the street before any more damage occurs.&acirc;",
        "_id": "8",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Minutes after the killing, there was a drive-by shooting on Presland Road at Whitton Private. Two&Acirc;&nbsp;people&Acirc;&nbsp;were treated for minor injuries and released.",
        "_id": "9",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Another drive-by shooting happened at 5:15 a.m. in the 2600 block of Innes Road. No one was hurt when a house was shot at several times. Police believe it happened at a post-clubbing after-party but do not yet know if it&acirc;s related to the ByWard Market shooting..",
        "_id": "10",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Finally, shots were exchanged between two vehicles near Ogilvie Road and Cummings Avenue in Overbrook at 4:50 p.m. Police&Acirc;&nbsp;are looking for&Acirc;&nbsp;a grey Nissan Altima, they recovered an&Acirc;&nbsp;older-model silver Ford Mustang with an air intake on its hood and blacked-out headlights.",
        "_id": "11",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "It is&Acirc;&nbsp;only sheer luck that no bystanders&Acirc;&nbsp;were hurt, Sweet said.",
        "_id": "12",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Repeatedly, he said that cooperation of victims was a &acirc;challenge&acirc; for police.",
        "_id": "13",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Chief Charles Bordeleau said that while he understands&Acirc;&nbsp;residents&Acirc;&nbsp;are concerned,&Acirc;&nbsp;the incidents were targeted shootings involving criminal activity and gang members.",
        "_id": "14",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "&acirc;They are not random,&acirc; Bordeleau said at the Shaw Centre, where the Canadian Association of Chiefs of Police is holding its national meeting.",
        "_id": "15",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Bordeleau said that Ottawa is not alone as urban police forces see an increase in gang-related shootings. Ottawa Police is working with the RCMP and border forces to stem the flow of smuggled handguns, such as a recent arrest of someone bringing the illegal guns through Cornwall to Ottawa.",
        "_id": "16",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Bordeleau urged any witnesses to come forward despite what he called legitimate concerns that have been expressed about retribution for going to police.",
        "_id": "17",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "&acirc;We can do things to prevent that,&acirc; he said, urging anyone with information to &acirc;take that one step.&acirc;",
        "_id": "18",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "The chief said that police are working to ensure that Ottawa, which will soon be the focus of the nation&acirc;s 150th birthday celebrations, remains a safe city.",
        "_id": "19",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "&acirc;That&acirc;s not something we can do alone,&acirc; he said. &acirc;We need help from the community.&acirc;",
        "_id": "20",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Mayor Jim Watson said Monday the weekend shootings were alarming.",
        "_id": "21",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "&acirc;There&acirc;s no question the situation on the weekend was very frightening and very disturbing. Even though Ottawa is a safe community by all standards in North America &acirc; one of the safest &acirc; when you see that kind of violence and murder and guns being shot randomly, that&acirc;s a concern,&acirc; Watson said.",
        "_id": "22",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "It&acirc;s why police budgeted to hire 25 new officers&Acirc;&nbsp;this year and the city put more money into anti-gang initiatives, Watson said.",
        "_id": "23",
        "paragraph": "open",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "<br>",
        "_id": "24",
        "type": "raw_html",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": " Watson is encouraging people to call police with any information to help investigators. Families should be pressured to find out if their children have guns, he said.",
        "_id": "25",
        "paragraph": "close",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "&acirc;If they know their child has a gun, they should be contacting the police. There&acirc;s no room for people to have handguns in an urban setting like the City of Ottawa,&acirc; Watson said.",
        "_id": "26",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "&acirc;We are a safe city, but people don&acirc;t feel safe when they see this kind of brazen activity taking place in a crowded bar or residential street.&acirc;",
        "_id": "27",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      }
