    "status": "published",
    "titles": {
      "main": "Police searching for 2 cars after four Sunday shooting incidents"
    },
    "content_elements": [
      {
        "height": 630,
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ],
        "type": "image",
        "width": 840,
        "title": "Image title",
        "_id": "1",
        "url": "http://wpmedia.ottawacitizen.com/2016/08/no-iptc-info-found3.jpeg?quality=55&strip=all&w=840&h=630&crop=1"
      },
      {
        "content": "On a frenetic day for first responders, one man died after being shot in Ottawa and there were another three shooting incidents, including one that left a 25-year-old man with serious injuries.",
        "_id": "2",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "At about 3:20 a.m., Omar Rashid-Ghader, 33, died after being shot multiple times inside&Acirc;&nbsp;a ByWard Market nightclub.",
        "_id": "3",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "At about 3:30 a.m., police said a drive-by shooting took place on Presland Road at Whitton Private, sending a passenger in a car to hospital, where he was treated and released.",
        "_id": "4",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Police said another drive-by shooting occurred at 5:15 a.m. in the 2600 block of Innes Road, but said no one was injured when a house was shot at several times.",
        "_id": "5",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "The day&acirc;s fourth shooting, at about 4:50 p.m. near the Overbrook neighbourhood, left police looking for two cars after it was believed that several shots had been fired from them. No one was injured in the incident&Acirc;&nbsp;near Ogilvie Road and Cummings Avenue.",
        "_id": "6",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 1\"> <div class=\"layoutArea\"> <div class=\"column\"> <p>One car was said to be a grey Nissan Altima and the other was described as an older-model silver Ford Mustang with an air intake on its hood and blacked out headlights.</p> </div> </div> </div>",
        "_id": "7",
        "type": "raw_html",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Police were asking anyone who saw the vehicles or knows where they are to call 911.",
        "_id": "8",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 1\"> <div class=\"layoutArea\"> <div class=\"column\"> <p>Anyone with information about any of the cases was asked to contact the guns and gangs unit at 613-236-1222 ext. 5050.</p> <div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 1\"> <div class=\"layoutArea\"> <div class=\"column\"> <p>Anonymous tips can be submitted by calling Crime Stoppers toll-free at 1-800-222-8477(TIPS) or by downloading the Ottawa police app.</p> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div>",
        "_id": "9",
        "type": "raw_html",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "&nbsp;",
