    "origin_url": "http://ottawacitizen.wpdev5.canada.com/business/local-business/ryan-lochte-really-was-robbed-at-gunpoint-in-brazil-i-put-my-hands-up-i-was-like-whatever/wcm/4dc0541d-2040-446f-8402-a9cb8fd64be4",
    "status": "published",
    "titles": {
      "main": "Ryann Lochte really was robbed at gunpoint in Brazil: ‘I put my hands up, I was like, ‘whatever’"
    },
    "content_elements": [
      {
        "content": "<h1 class=\"npStorySEOTitle\"></h1>",
        "_id": "1",
        "type": "raw_html",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "<div class=\"npBlock npPostContent\"> <div> <p>RIO DE JANEIRO â Olympian Ryan Lochte and three other members of the U.S. swimming team were robbed at gunpoint âby individuals posing as armed police officersâ in Brazil. The U.S. Olympic Committee confirmed swirling reports Sunday.<a href=\"http://www.nbcnews.com/storyline/2016-rio-summer-olympics/u-s-swimmer-ryan-lochte-robbed-gunpoint-brazil-n630396?cid=sm_tw\">Lochte confirmed it himself</a> in an interview with NBC News.</p> <p>âWe got pulled over, in the taxi, and these guys came out with a badge, a police badge, no lights, no nothing just a police badge and they pulled us over,â <a href=\"http://www.nbcnews.com/storyline/2016-rio-summer-olympics/u-s-swimmer-ryan-lochte-robbed-gunpoint-brazil-n630396?cid=sm_tw\">Lochte said to the network</a>. âThey pulled out their guns, they told the other swimmers to get down on the ground â they got down on the ground. I refused, I was like we didnât do anything wrong, so â Iâm not getting down on the ground.</p> <p>âAnd then the guy pulled out his gun, he cocked it, put it to my forehead and he said, âGet down,â and I put my hands up, I was like âwhatever.â He took our money, he took my wallet â he left my cell phone, he left my credentials.â</p> <p>Along with Lochte, Gunnar Bentz, Jack Conger and Jimmy Feigen were in a taxi that was stopped and held up, USOC spokesperson Patrick Sandusky said. All four athletes are safe.</p> <div id=\"fsk_splitbox_9\" class=\" fsk_splitbox_9\"></div> <p>Brazilian swimmer Thiago Pereiraâs representative told The Post earlier on Sunday that Lochte was in a taxi leaving Club France on the Rodrigo de Freitas lagoon when the vehicle was robbed. <a href=\"http://oglobo.globo.com/esportes/medalhista-olimpico-tem-arma-apontada-para-ele-apos-deixar-festa-diz-fox-news-19920003\" target=\"_blank\">Video on O Globo</a> shows Lochte and Pereira at what appears to be a rave.</p> <p>FlÃ¡vio Perez said the incident, in which Lochte was unharmed, occurred after a birthday celebration at a Brazilian club.</p> <p>âThiago Pereira and his wife Gabriela Pauletti were in Club France, the French house in Brazil, and they were celebrating the birthday of a friend in common,â said Perez, Pereiraâs spokesman.</p> <p>âLochte was also in the same place, commemorating the same birthday. Ryan and Thiago are friends. Thiago and his wife left earlier, they left alone, the two of them. Thiago and his wife went back to their hotel. Then Thiago, on finding out what happened, called Ryan. Ryan is well, and Thiago said that the robbery, according to Ryan, was in the taxi. The taxi was robbed.â</p> <div class=\"npImgCentre\"> <div class=\"npPosRel\"> <p><img class=\"size-large wp-image-1181302\" src=\"http://wpmedia.news.nationalpost.com/2016/08/149444526.jpg?w=620&amp;quality=65&amp;strip=all&amp;h=413\" alt=\"Al Bello / Getty Images\" width=\"620\" height=\"413\"></p> <div class=\"npPhotoTxt npTxtPlain npTxtLeft\"> <div class=\"npGroup\">\n<span class=\"npPhotoCredit\">Al Bello / Getty Images</span><span class=\"npPhotoCaption\">Pereira (left) and Lochte in a 2012 file photo from the London Olympics.</span>\n</div> </div> </div> </div> <p>A spokesman for Club France, Hugo Sppezapria, said that Lochte, Pereira and friends attended a party inside Club France â a large establishment along the lagoon with sports fields, a place to ride horses, and food and clothing vendors â into the early morning hours Sunday. The party, which began around 11:30 p.m., took place at a venue inside the club called the Picadeiro Armando de Alencar and was hosted by CafÃ© de la Musique. Some 2,500 people attended.</p> <p>Sppezapria said that Lochte and Pereira left the party together between 2:30 and 3 a.m. and visited another âcommunity.â</p> <p>âWhy the hell would they do that?â Sppezapria said.</p> <p>Sppezapria said he didnât know where the alleged robbery took place.</p> <p>Brazilian police issued the following statement Sunday afternoon: âThe Civil Police were not notified about the robbery which an American swimmer suffered after leaving a party. The institution is investigating the incident, on the base of information circulated by the press. The American Consulate was contacted and said it had not been notified either. The International Olympic Committee (IOC) said that the US Committee denied the crime. The investigation is in progress.â</p> <blockquote class=\"pullquote\"><p>Ryan is well, and Thiago said that the robbery, according to Ryan, was in the taxi. The taxi was robbed</p></blockquote> <p>Reports of the incident conflicted Sunday morning. Mark Adams, the IOCâs director of communications, told reporters in Rio that the report is ânot true,â but Lochteâs mother confirmed it <a href=\"http://www.usatoday.com/story/sports/olympics/rio-2016/2016/08/14/olympic-swimmer-ryan-lochte-held-up-gunpoint-rio/88715436/\" target=\"_blank\">for USA Today</a>.</p> <p>âI think theyâre all shaken up. There were a few of them,â Ileana Lochte said. âNo, they were just, they just took their wallets and basically that was it.â</p> <p>David Marsh, Lochteâs personal coach and the head womenâs coach for the U.S. swim team, also texted USA Today to deny the report. Finally, Lochte himself confirmed the report to NBC.</p> <p>Fox Sports News in Australia initially quoted Lochteâs mother describing the encounter as âterrifyingâ and she said she was en route to meet him. Lochte reportedly had been invited to a party by Pereira and was accompanied by three teammates. Foxâs Ben Way reported that Lochte was ârobbed of his wallet.â</p> <p>Earlier, another Rio Olympics spokesman said he had heard there âwas an issueâ involving Lochte but could not confirm the details.</p> <p>Lochte, 32, is a six-time Olympic gold medalist. He and the U.S. team won gold in the 4Ã200-metre freestyle. Lochte has not been in an event since Thursday and swimming events ended Saturday night.</p> <p><em>With files from National Post Staff</em></p> </div> </div>",
