        "content": "<div id=\"maincontent\"> <div id=\"content\" class=\"content\"> <div class=\"paddle previous loaded\"> <div class=\"headline \"> <p> </p> </div> </div> <article class=\"articlecontent loaded\"><section class=\"articlebody\"><span class=\"storyimage fullwidth inlineimage\"> <span class=\"image\"> <img class=\" loaded\" src=\"http://img-s-msn-com.akamaized.net/tenant/amp/entityid/BBvczrX.img?h=329&amp;w=624&amp;m=6&amp;q=60&amp;o=f&amp;l=f&amp;x=742&amp;y=428\" alt=\"\" width=\"624\"></span> <span class=\"caption truncate\"> <span class=\"attribution\">Â© Provided by The Huffington Post</span> </span> </span>Over a decade has passed since the series finale aired, butÂ <a href=\"http://www.huffingtonpost.com/news/friends/?ncid=txtlnkusaolp00000618\" target=\"_blank\">âFriendsâ</a> continues to be one of the most relevant television shows, with <a href=\"http://www.vulture.com/2016/03/20-somethings-streaming-friends-c-v-r.html?ncid=txtlnkusaolp00000618\" target=\"_blank\">teenagers binging episodes on Netflix</a> and media-trained Disney stars of todayÂ <a href=\"http://glittermagrocks.com/connect/2015/07/04/interview-with-jordan-fisher-2/?ncid=txtlnkusaolp00000618\" target=\"_blank\">naming it as their favorite show</a>.So given itâs continued popularity, thereâs a decent chance that, even in 2016, you still have a stake in the most heartbreaking thing to happen on the show â when Phoebe (<a href=\"http://www.huffingtonpost.com/news/lisa-kudrow/?ncid=txtlnkusaolp00000618\" target=\"_blank\">Lisa Kudrow</a>) and DavidÂ (<a href=\"http://www.huffingtonpost.com/news/hank-azaria/?ncid=txtlnkusaolp00000618\" target=\"_blank\">Hank Azaria</a>)Â didnât end up together. After David decided to go to the Belarus capital city Minsk for his career, Phoebe married Mike (<a href=\"http://www.huffingtonpost.com/news/paul-rudd/?ncid=txtlnkusaolp00000618\" target=\"_blank\">Paul Rudd</a>) â a fine choice â but it was still a sad end for the science-loving, glasses-wearing character.Well, perhaps it comes as even more tragic news that it wasnât even supposed to be that way.In a <a href=\"http://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/hank-azaria-emmys_us_579a7918e4b08a8e8b5d553a?ec4unv74q5v4r0ms4i&amp;ncid=txtlnkusaolp00000618\" target=\"_blank\">recent interview</a> with Azaria about his Emmy nomination for a role in âRay Donovan,âÂ The Huffington Post asked the actor what the Minsk happened. And apparently … <h4>David and Phoebe <em>were</em> supposed to end up together, but Paul Rudd was too charming to write out.</h4> <p><span class=\"storyimage fullwidth inlineimage\"> <span class=\"image\"> <img class=\" loaded\" src=\"http://img-s-msn-com.akamaized.net/tenant/amp/entityid/BBvcuMG.img?h=407&amp;w=624&amp;m=6&amp;q=60&amp;o=f&amp;l=f&amp;x=1059&amp;y=558\" alt=\"\" width=\"624\"></span> <span class=\"caption truncate\"> <span class=\"attribution\">Â© Provided by The Huffington Post</span> </span> </span>Responding to whether he knew it would be the end of Davidâs arc when he went to Minsk, Azaria told HuffPost, âNo, I didnât know that was the end of David. The plan always was kind of to bring him back.â</p> <p>David does return in a small capacity on the show, but Azaria specifically meant that he was under the impression Phoebe and David would end up together.</p> <p>âI think, honestly, what happened was Paul Rudd is so awesome that they sort of found a groove with him and [my character] became more of just the grist for that mill,â said Azaria, who added, âAs opposed to the other way around.â</p> <p>Was the actor as upset as his character to lose out to Paul Rudd?</p> <p>âIt actually did sting a little bit,â said Azaria. âWhatever part of me is David the science guy who went to Minsk, which admittedly is probably a small part of me [<em>laughs</em>],Â but that part of me wanted to end up with Phoebe. So I was sort of sad when I didnât.â</p> <div class=\"xnetvidplayer\"></div> </section></article>\n</div> </div>",
