    "origin_url": "http://ottawacitizen.wpdev5.canada.com/news/local-news/no-jail-for-chiropractor-who-sexually-abused-patients/wcm/4ad8d2dd-441f-4dee-b166-6df9db23ef80",
    "status": "published",
    "titles": {
      "main": "No jail for chiropractor who sexually abused patients"
    },
    "content_elements": [
      {
        "content": "An Ottawa chiropractor who sexually abused three patients won&acirc;t spend any time behind bars after a judge sentenced him Tuesday to house arrest and a curfew rather than jail.",
        "_id": "1",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Victims of Michael Beaton groaned as Ontario Superior Court Justice Douglas Rutherford sentenced the 77-year-old retired chiropractor to a 15-month conditional sentence. Beaton will serve less than half of that sentence &acirc; or seven months &acirc; under house arrest. The other eight months will be spent under conditions that include a curfew from 7 p.m. to 7 a.m., although Beaton will be free to come and go as he pleases during the rest of the day.",
        "_id": "2",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Beaton had been convicted of indecently assaulting two male patients in the late 1970s or early 1980s for grabbing their genitals during chiropractic treatments at his Baseline Road office. He was also found guilty of sexually assaulting another patient in 2003 during a chiropractic treatment that occurred at Beaton&acirc;s home.",
        "_id": "3",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Although Canada&acirc;s Criminal Code was changed in 2012 to make jail time mandatory for sexual assault, Beaton benefitted from a section of Canada&acirc;s Charter of Rights and Freedoms that allows a judge to sentence an offender under the laws that existed at the time of the offence.",
        "_id": "4",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Despite the severity of the Beaton&acirc;s crimes on vulnerable patients, Rutherford found a conditional sentence was appropriate after a psychiatrist testified Beaton presented a low risk to reoffend and a conditional sentence wouldn&acirc;t put public safety at risk. Beaton no longer holds a license to practice, and his conditional sentence includes an order not to provide any chiropractic services.",
        "_id": "5",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "<div id=\"fsk_splitbox_1715\" class=\" fsk_splitbox_1715\"></div>",
        "_id": "6",
        "type": "raw_html",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Beaton was placed on probation for a year, added to the sex offender registry for life and ordered to provide a sample of his DNA to the national databank. Beaton must also complete 100 hours of community service and stay away from his victims.",
        "_id": "7",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "The sentence caused dismay for one of Beaton&acirc;s victims.",
        "_id": "8",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "&acirc;It would be nice for this man to experience what it would be like to do jail time,&acirc; said the 59-year-old man who can&acirc;t be identified because of a court-ordered publication ban.",
        "_id": "9",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "&acirc;If I had been in his position and committed a murder, I would be sentenced to life,&acirc; he said. &acirc;He&acirc;s still basically able to do whatever he wants to do.&acirc;",
        "_id": "10",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Under conditions of Beaton&acirc;s house arrest, he can go out for groceries and other necessities twice a week and attend religious services once a week. He is also allowed to leave his home for medical appointments or if approved by his probation officer.",
        "_id": "11",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Another disabled man who came forward with allegations of abuse against Beaton, only to have the judge acquit the doctor of the charge because he felt it may have been an approved treatment, said he felt like it was &acirc;different justice&acirc; for Beaton because of his age.",
        "_id": "12",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "&acirc;If he was 40 he would have gone to jail,&acirc; added the man&acirc;s wife. Court heard Beaton has showed no sign of remorse and has refused to take responsibility or seek treatment.",
        "_id": "13",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "&acirc;Those are only numbers,&acirc; she said of Beaton&acirc;s age and the years passed since the time of the offence. &acirc;It shouldn&acirc;t matter.&acirc;",
        "_id": "14",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Rutherford seemed aware his sentence of strict house arrest may not seem severe enough.",
        "_id": "15",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "&acirc;Some think it is a piece of cake and it might be in comparison to serving seven months in a prison, especially at your age Mr. Beaton,&acirc; said Rutherford.",
        "_id": "16",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Rutherford said it is more difficult than it appears, since Beaton must essentially be his own jailer. Breaking the rules could mean serving the rest of his sentence in jail, Rutherford said.",
        "_id": "17",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Rutherford said while Beaton&acirc;s crimes represented &acirc;serious violations of the person and the integrity of the complainants,&acirc; they lie at the less serious end of the spectrum given their brevity and lack of violence and threats.",
        "_id": "18",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "However, they were still &acirc;serious breaches of trust&acirc; committed by a trusted health profession.",
        "_id": "19",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      }
