    "origin_url": "http://ottawacitizen.wpdev5.canada.com/business/local-business/rio-olympics-2016-australia-refuse-to-move-into-athletes-village/wcm/aabeb951-309d-4736-98dc-9930ee53ca7d",
    "status": "published",
    "titles": {
      "main": "Rio Olympics 2016: Australia move into athletes' village"
    },
    "content_elements": [
      {
        "content": "Australia are refusing to move their athletes into the Rio Olympic Village because of concerns about the state of their accommodation.",
        "_id": "1",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Problems include &ldquo;blocked toilets, leaking pipes and exposed wiring&rdquo;, according to team boss Kitty Chiller.",
        "_id": "2",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Chiller said she had raised concerns with local event organisers and the International Olympic Committee, and was &ldquo;pushing hard for a solution&rdquo;.",
        "_id": "3",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Australian staff are in nearby hotels with the first athletes due on Monday.",
        "_id": "4",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Alternative accommodation for team members arriving over the next three days has been arranged.",
        "_id": "5",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "The $1.5bn (&Acirc;&pound;1.14bn) 31-building village has tennis courts, football pitches, seven swimming pools and will house 18,000 athletes and officials at the height of the Games, which start on 5 August, less than two weeks away.",
        "_id": "6",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Chiller, the head of Australia&rsquo;s Olympic delegation, said extra maintenance staff and more than 1,000 cleaners have been engaged to fix the problems but the faults, particularly the plumbing issues, have not been resolved.",
        "_id": "7",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "She said ",
        "_id": "8",
        "paragraph": "open",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "<a href=\"http://rio2016.olympics.com.au/news/village-not-safe-or-ready-chiller-statement\" class=\"sp-story-body__external-link\">in a statement on the Australian Olympic website<i class=\"sp-story-body__external-link-icon gelicon gelicon--external\"></i></a>",
        "_id": "9",
        "type": "raw_html",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": ": &ldquo;Due to a variety of problems in the Village, including gas, electricity and plumbing, I have decided that no Australian team member will move into our allocated building.",
        "_id": "10",
        "paragraph": "close",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "&ldquo;Problems include blocked toilets, leaking pipes, exposed wiring, darkened stairwells where no lighting has been installed and dirty floors in need of a massive clean.&rdquo;",
        "_id": "11",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Organisers have conceded there have been &ldquo;teething troubles&rdquo; and promised that crews would be &ldquo;working 24 hours a day until the issues are resolved&rdquo;.",
        "_id": "12",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "But Rio Mayor Eduardo Paes responded to Australian criticism by saying the Village is &ldquo;more beautiful&rdquo; than Sydney for the 2000 Games and that he was about to put &ldquo;a kangaroo jumping outside&rdquo; to &ldquo;make them feel at home&rdquo;.",
        "_id": "13",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "The New Zealand team boss Rob Waddell said he was &ldquo;disappointed&rdquo; the Village was not ready, adding &ldquo;it hasn&rsquo;t been easy&rdquo;, but said with &ldquo;a bit of hard work&rdquo;, their facilities were ready for the first athletes arrival.",
        "_id": "14",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "&ldquo;Our team has had to get stuck in to get the job done,&rdquo; said Waddell.",
        "_id": "15",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Italy&rsquo;s Carlo Mornati said his team were hiring labourers, electricians, plumbers and bricklayers to bring the apartments &ldquo;up to normal conditions as soon as possible&rdquo;.",
        "_id": "16",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "The British team have had staff in place for several days and a spokesman told Reuters: &ldquo;We are confident that our accommodation is ready to receive athletes and will be to the highest standards within the village.",
        "_id": "17",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "&ldquo;Whilst we have encountered some maintenance difficulties this is not uncommon with new build structures of this type and we have been working hard to overcome them.&rdquo;",
        "_id": "18",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "And the US Olympic Committee said there were &ldquo;minor issues,&rdquo; but that it was no different to &ldquo;every Games&rdquo;.",
        "_id": "19",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "&nbsp;",
        "_id": "20",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "&nbsp;",
        "_id": "21",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      }
