    "origin_url": "http://ottawacitizen.wpdev5.canada.com/business/local-business/five-things-you-should-know-before-you-start-your-work-day-on-july-13/wcm/6d9d5c35-54d5-44e8-bc6d-920124b3e647",
    "status": "published",
    "titles": {
      "main": "Five things you should know before you start your work day on July 13"
    },
    "content_elements": [
      {
        "content": "Good morning. U.S. safety regulators are demanding Autopilot info from Tesla Motors following a May 7 fatal crash. TV revenue remains stable despite falling subscriptions. And will tipping in restaurants become a thing of the past? These stories and more in your morning cheat sheet to the Financial Post.",
        "_id": "1",
        "paragraph": "open",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "<br>",
        "_id": "2",
        "type": "raw_html",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": " 1. Who needs tipping&acirc;&brvbar; if there&acirc;s a 16% hospitality charge?",
        "_id": "3",
        "paragraph": "none",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "<br>",
        "_id": "4",
        "type": "raw_html",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": " Gavin Young/Postmedia",
        "_id": "5",
        "paragraph": "none",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "<br>",
        "_id": "6",
        "type": "raw_html",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": " Gavin Young/PostmediaServers work during the busy lunch hour at the Earls.67 restaurant in downtown Calgary on Monday July 11, 2016. Instead of the traditional tipping method the rebranded location is testing a new 16 per cent hospitality charge to all bills.",
        "_id": "7",
        "paragraph": "close",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Put away your coins and don&acirc;t bother ending your meal with hurried math to determine an appropriate gratuity &acirc; a new Calgary restaurant doesn&acirc;t want your tip, Annalise Klingbeil reports.",
        "_id": "8",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "The 67th Earls Restaurant location in North America is a &acirc;prototype concept&acirc; where new ideas for the chain will be tested, including ditching tipping.",
        "_id": "9",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "When diners finish their meals at Earls.67 on Stephen Avenue, their bill will contain a 16 per cent &acirc;hospitality charge&acirc; and no room for a gratuity, in a move management believes could become a lot more common in the future.",
        "_id": "10",
        "paragraph": "open",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "<br>",
        "_id": "11",
        "type": "raw_html",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": " 2. U.S. safety agency seeks answers on fatal Tesla Autopilot crash",
        "_id": "12",
        "paragraph": "none",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "<br>",
        "_id": "13",
        "type": "raw_html",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": " Getty Images",
        "_id": "14",
        "paragraph": "none",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "<br>",
        "_id": "15",
        "type": "raw_html",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": " Getty ImagesWhen Tesla launched Autopilot in October, it said the system would allow the vehicle &acirc;to steer within a lane, change lanes with the simple tap of a turn signal, and manage speed by using active, traffic-aware cruise control.&acirc;",
        "_id": "16",
        "paragraph": "close",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "U.S. highway safety regulators have demanded that Tesla Motors Inc hand over detailed information about the design, operation and testing of its Autopilot technology following a May 7 fatal crash in which the system was in use, David Shepardson reports.",
        "_id": "17",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "The U.S. National Highway Traffic Safety Administration, investigating an accident that&acirc;s increased scrutiny of automated driving technology, also wants to know what Tesla investigators have learned about the crash.",
        "_id": "18",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Joshua Brown was killed when his vehicle, operating on Autopilot in Florida, drove under a tractor trailer. It was first known fatality to involve a Model S operating on the Autopilot system that takes control of steering and braking in certain conditions.",
        "_id": "19",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "The agency is seeking details of all design changes and updates to Autopilot since it went into use last year, and information on whether Tesla plans updates in the next four months.",
        "_id": "20",
        "paragraph": "open",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "<br>",
        "_id": "21",
        "type": "raw_html",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": " 3. GDP growth of 26% isn&acirc;t all it&acirc;s cracked up to be&acirc;&brvbar;",
        "_id": "22",
        "paragraph": "none",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "<br>",
        "_id": "23",
        "type": "raw_html",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": " Peter Muhly/AFP/Getty Images",
        "_id": "24",
        "paragraph": "none",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "<br>",
        "_id": "25",
        "type": "raw_html",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": " Peter Muhly/AFP/Getty ImagesIreland&rsquo;s economy grew 26 per cent in 2015, the Central Statistics Office said.",
        "_id": "26",
        "paragraph": "close",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Ireland&acirc;s economy grew 26 per cent in 2015, officials from the Central Statistics Office told a stunned room full of economists and reporters in Dublin on Tuesday. Previously, they estimated growth of 7.8 per cent, Dara Doyle reports.",
        "_id": "27",
        "paragraph": "open",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "<br>",
        "_id": "28",
        "type": "raw_html",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": " Advertisement",
        "_id": "29",
        "paragraph": "close",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "The figure is mostly explained by the open nature of Ireland&acirc;s economy and its attraction to U.S. companies seeking access to a 12.5 per cent tax rate. Among firms that have inverted to Ireland, mostly through acquisitions, are Perrigo Co. and Jazz Pharmaceuticals Plc. Corporations with assets overseas of 523 billion euros (US$580 billion) were headquartered in Ireland in 2014, up from 391 billion euros in 2013, according to the statistics office.",
        "_id": "30",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Finance Minister Michael Noonan pointed out that growth numbers cut Ireland&acirc;s debt and deficit ratios. Trouble is, they carry downsides too.",
        "_id": "31",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "For one, tax inversions artificially inflate the size of Ireland&acirc;s economy. When the headquarters of a group of companies becomes resident in Ireland, all of its global profits may be counted as part of the nation&acirc;s gross national income, according to the ministry.",
        "_id": "32",
        "paragraph": "open",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "<br>",
        "_id": "33",
        "type": "raw_html",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": " 4. TV revenue stable despite subscriptions falling in 2015",
        "_id": "34",
        "paragraph": "none",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "<br>",
        "_id": "35",
        "type": "raw_html",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": " Fotolia",
        "_id": "36",
        "paragraph": "none",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "<br>",
        "_id": "37",
        "type": "raw_html",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": " FotoliaIt&acirc;s the third year in a row television subscriptions have declined as streaming services such as Netflix boast huge gains, with a million Canadians estimated to have signed up for the U.S. online video service between June 2015 and April 2016 alone for a total of more than five million subscribers",
        "_id": "38",
        "paragraph": "close",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Nearly 160,000 Canadians cut their television subscriptions last year, but more cash from each customer dulled the buzz kill for providers, Emily Jackson reports.",
        "_id": "39",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "The overall number of TV subscribers dropped to 11.2 million as of Aug. 31, 2015 from 11.4 million in 2014, according to the Canadian Radio-television and Telecommunications Commission.",
        "_id": "40",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "It&acirc;s the third year in a row subscriptions have declined as streaming services such as Netflix boast huge gains, with a million Canadians estimated to have signed up for the U.S. online video service between June 2015 and April 2016 alone for a total of more than five million subscribers, according to Toronto-based Solutions Research Group.",
        "_id": "41",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Still, television providers reported a revenue drop of only 0.1 per cent &acirc; total revenue was steady at $8.9 billion &acirc; as average revenue per user climbed to $66.08 from $65.25.",
        "_id": "42",
        "paragraph": "open",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "<br>",
        "_id": "43",
        "type": "raw_html",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": " 5. What does the future hold for GM in Oshawa?",
        "_id": "44",
        "paragraph": "none",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "<br>",
        "_id": "45",
        "type": "raw_html",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": " THE CANADIAN PRESS/Frank Gunn",
        "_id": "46",
        "paragraph": "none",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "<br>",
        "_id": "47",
        "type": "raw_html",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": " THE CANADIAN PRESS/Frank Gunn A worker checks the paint on a car at the GM factory in Oshawa, Ontario",
        "_id": "48",
        "paragraph": "close",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "General Motors Co.&acirc;s plants in Oshawa, Ont. have been lurching along on life support for about 11 years but their luck may be about to run out, Kristine Owram reports.",
        "_id": "49",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Under current plans, the popular Chevrolet Equinox crossover won&acirc;t be produced at the consolidated plant after next year, while the neighbouring flex plant has no product slated for it beyond 2019. GM shifted production of the Chevrolet Camaro to Lansing, Mich., last November, cutting 1,000 jobs.",
        "_id": "50",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Perhaps most worrisome, the commitments made by GM Canada as part of its 2009 government bailout, including a promise to maintain at least 16 per cent of its North American production in Canada, lapse this year.",
        "_id": "51",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Steve Carlisle, president of GM Canada, has said repeatedly that Oshawa&acirc;s future depends on labour negotiations with the company&acirc;s workers, represented by Unifor, which will get underway in mid-August. Unifor president Jerry Dias has said workers will strike if GM doesn&acirc;t allocate any new products to the city.",
        "_id": "52",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      }
