    "origin_url": "http://ottawacitizen.wpdev5.canada.com/news/local-news/well-this-is-the-way-calvin-is-going-to-croak-the-tweed-fair-saviour-in-his-own-words/wcm/30fb9494-78c1-428a-8900-3a401f99a5de",
    "status": "published",
    "titles": {
      "main": "'Well, this is the way Calvin is going to croak' — The Tweed Fair saviour in his own words"
    },
    "content_elements": [
      {
        "content": "Calvin Stein says he&acirc;s no hero, but&Acirc;&nbsp;it was his quick action and horse instinct that saved a three-year-old girl from being trampled by a runaway team of horses&Acirc;&nbsp;at the Tweed Fair on Saturday. Stein, 51, of Madoc, was harnessing his own team waiting for his turn to compete&Acirc;&nbsp;at the fair&acirc;s horse pull competition when he saw a team break free from their handler and head into a crowd of onlookers.",
        "_id": "1",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "<strong>Q: Can you tell us what happened?<br></strong>",
        "_id": "2",
        "type": "raw_html",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "<strong>A:</strong>",
        "_id": "3",
        "type": "raw_html",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": " &acirc;It&acirc;s unfortunate. The team got away from a gentleman. I was standing at my trailer waiting for our turn in the ring.&Acirc;&nbsp;Anyway, the team came running and my instincts was to try to catch the team. I knew how to read them. I knew the direction they were going and I knew where they were headed.",
        "_id": "4",
        "paragraph": "close",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "&acirc;I saw a father standing there with three kids talking to another teamster. He had one on either side of him and the other was standing beside the other guy on his right-hand side. I ran as fast as I could screaming and everybody started to scatter. The father had ahold of two of them and the three year old was just standing there, oblivious to what was going on.",
        "_id": "5",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "&acirc;I just swooped the young lady up and I just basically&Acirc;&nbsp;&acirc;&Acirc;&nbsp;I knew they were close&Acirc;&nbsp;&acirc;&Acirc;&nbsp;I just threw her. I knew she&acirc;d bounce, she maybe&acirc;d break and arm or a leg. I guess that&acirc;s not what you&acirc;re supposed to do &acirc;&Acirc;&nbsp;throw kids &acirc; but&Acirc;&nbsp;I just threw her and the team mowed me over. I flipped and flopped and the rest is history. The young lady was taken to hospital &acirc;&Acirc;&nbsp;she&acirc;s fine, a few bumps and bruises, very fortunate.",
        "_id": "6",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "<strong>Q: What about you? Were you injured?</strong>",
        "_id": "7",
        "type": "raw_html",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "<strong>A:</strong>",
        "_id": "8",
        "type": "raw_html",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": " I&acirc;ve got a broken orbital socket, concussion, a bunch of stitches in the face. I&acirc;m going to carry some dirty scars. And I&acirc;ve got one eye that&acirc;s a little screwed up.",
        "_id": "9",
        "paragraph": "close",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "<strong>Q: Wow. The police described it as âminor injuries.â</strong>",
        "_id": "10",
        "type": "raw_html",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "<strong>A:</strong>",
        "_id": "11",
        "type": "raw_html",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": " That&acirc;s what I told him. I&acirc;m fine. I can heal.&Acirc;&nbsp;I&acirc;m very optimistic.",
        "_id": "12",
        "paragraph": "close",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "<strong>Q: Could you see the horses coming? Did they trample you from behind?</strong>",
        "_id": "13",
        "type": "raw_html",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "<strong>A:</strong>",
        "_id": "14",
        "type": "raw_html",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": " From the side. I tried to do it all in one motion. Pick her up and run. But by the time I picked her up they were on top of me, so I just threw her.&Acirc;&nbsp;Someone told me that it looked like, you know, when you have a child sitting in your lap in a car accident and how they get ejected? They thought she got ejected. But I remember throwing her. I remember everything. I wasn&acirc;t knocked out or nothing.",
        "_id": "15",
        "paragraph": "close",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "I just remember laying on the ground. When I hit the ground and the blood pooling by my head. I thought it was over. I thought, &acirc;Well, this is the way Calvin&acirc;s going to croak.&acirc;",
        "_id": "16",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "But I got excellent, excellent health care. Everyone complains about health care, until they need it. Well, I needed it. That stay in the hospital was nothing.",
        "_id": "17",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "<strong>Q: Where did you go to hospital?</strong>",
        "_id": "18",
        "type": "raw_html",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "<strong>A:</strong>",
        "_id": "19",
        "type": "raw_html",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": " They took me to Belleville. That was my request. They were going to fly me to Toronto, then they were going to fly me to Kingston. But they couldn&acirc;t get the helicopter landed at the fairground because of all the animals. So I talked to the EMS, I said, &acirc;I can tell you there&acirc;s something broken in my face, but the rest of me is just muscle bruising.&acirc; So they took me down and ran me through their CAT scans and other run of the mill stuff.",
        "_id": "20",
        "paragraph": "close",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "<strong>Q: Do you consider yourself a hero?</strong>",
        "_id": "21",
        "type": "raw_html",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "<strong>A:</strong>",
        "_id": "22",
        "type": "raw_html",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": " It just happened. It was an accident. I&acirc;m just glad I was there to save the kid.",
        "_id": "23",
        "paragraph": "close",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Somebody called me a hero. But if you&acirc;re going to write anything, you can put this down: &acirc;I&acirc;m not a hero. The heroes are the men and women of our Canadian Forces, and the men and women of our police forces, and the men and women of our EMS. I&acirc;m just an average person that did what everybody should do. Look out for each other. That&acirc;s what I really&Acirc;&nbsp;believe.",
        "_id": "24",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "<strong>Q: Have you heard from the little girlâs family?</strong>",
        "_id": "25",
        "type": "raw_html",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "<strong>A:</strong>",
        "_id": "26",
        "type": "raw_html",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": " They wanted to see me but my brother told them to wait a few days. They sent me a couple of wonderful texts.&Acirc;&nbsp;They thanked me and said I was their saviour and the whole shooting match, but that&acirc;s not&acirc;&brvbar;. I&acirc;m just me.&acirc;",
        "_id": "27",
        "paragraph": "close",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "<a href=\"mailto:bcrawford@postmedia.com\">bcrawford@postmedia.com</a>",
        "_id": "28",
        "type": "raw_html",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
