      "main": "Police renew appeal for help finding missing girl, 15"
    },
    "content_elements": [
      {
        "content": "<div> <p>OttawaÂ police released a new photo of a missing 15-year-old girl Tuesday in hopes it will help them find the teen last spotted in Barrhaven nearly three months ago.</p> <p>Hayl Collis was seen April 22 in the 400 block of Longfields Drive. Police say her family is concerned about her well-being.</p> <p>She is described as a 5â4 and 110 lbs with long, light-brown hair, blue eyes and pierced ears.</p> <p>Anyone who knows Collisâ current location is asked to call Ottawa police dispatch at (613) 230-6211.</p> <p>Those with other information that could help investigators are asked to call the missing persons unit at (613) 236-1222 ext. 2355 between 8 a.m. and 4 p.m.</p> <p>Anonymous tips can be made to Crime Stoppers at (800) 222-8477 or by downloading the Ottawa police app.</p> </div>",
        "_id": "1",
