    "origin_url": "http://ottawacitizen.wpdev5.canada.com/news/local-news/latest-shooting-victim/wcm/9ca999f9-0502-4294-9eb3-42b82dde684b",
    "status": "published",
    "titles": {
      "main": "Latest Shooting Victim"
    },
    "content_elements": [
      {
        "content": "Grieving friends of a slain Montreal man gunned down in Lowertown early Sunday morning say they feared the teen who grew up on the streets would end up in jail or dead, but they weren&acirc;t prepared for it to have happened so soon.",
        "_id": "1",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Ottawa police were called to 292 St. Andrew St. shortly before 4 a.m. Sunday for reports of multiple gunshots fired outside. Tarique Leger, just 19, was shot in the chest, lying on the ground outside a short-term stay condo and without vital signs. Paramedics tried to revive him. He was pronounced dead at hospital.",
        "_id": "2",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Lifelong friend Dominic Leblanc said the two had known each other since they were three years old. Leblanc considered Leger a brother, but as they grew up he worried about his friend.",
        "_id": "3",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "&acirc;We&acirc;ve been raised in the street for all our life,&acirc; Leblanc said.",
        "_id": "4",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "&nbsp;",
        "_id": "5",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "&acirc;I knew he was to finish his life in jail or get shot but not that young.&acirc;",
        "_id": "6",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Leblanc said there were people who didn&acirc;t like Leger &acirc;because of what he was doing&acirc; but that he was someone Leblanc trusted.",
        "_id": "7",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "In February 2015, Leger, who used an alias on Facebook, posted a picture of a freezer bag and mason jar full of marijuana. &acirc;Making my moves my n&acirc;a,&acirc; the now-dead man wrote.",
        "_id": "8",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Leblanc knows Leger would&acirc;ve taken a bullet for him or others he loved. &acirc;He was always there to protect you, to help you out,&acirc; Leblanc said.",
        "_id": "9",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Another of Leger&acirc;s friends, who asked not to be identified, said Leger was a &acirc;good man&acirc; who had his struggles but at his core had a &acirc;good heart.&acirc;",
        "_id": "10",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "&acirc;He hung with the wrong crowd,&acirc; he said, and &acirc;lived a dangerous life.&acirc;",
        "_id": "11",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "In the end, friends believe that life caught up to him.",
        "_id": "12",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Leger grew up in Pointe-Saint-Charles, a working-class neighbourhood in Montreal&acirc;s southwest. Friends said he had potential and showed promise on both the football field and basketball court. But he chose &acirc;the gangster life.&acirc;",
        "_id": "13",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "His cousin,&Acirc;&nbsp;Shania Hoyte, reeling at the news of his death, posted online that she&acirc;d always told Tarique that the life he lived was dangerous. His reply, she wrote: &acirc;Either you watch me or live it with me.&acirc;",
        "_id": "14",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Leger was known to Montreal police. He was wanted on an arrest warrant by that force for a November 2015 robbery. The warrant was issued in March of this year. Leger has no criminal record in Ontario.",
        "_id": "15",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Leblanc believes Leger was in Montreal the day before he was shot, but left to stay in Ottawa. Police believe he came to Ottawa to party.",
        "_id": "16",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Leger rented an Airbnb unit on St. Andrew where he was staying during his visit to the capital.",
        "_id": "17",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "A friend who Leger was partying with at another location wondered online whether Leger would still be alive if she had told him it was too late to &acirc;do this.&acirc;",
        "_id": "18",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Leger is believed to have been partying with friends when he decided to head back to Montreal. His plan was to stop at the St. Andrew Street rental to pack his belongings. He was killed before making it anywhere else.",
        "_id": "19",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Investigators suspect his killing was targeted but had not yet determined whether it was drug- or even gang-related.",
        "_id": "20",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Police did seize a small amount of marijuana among Leger&acirc;s possessions.",
        "_id": "21",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Leger&acirc;s was the city&acirc;s ninth homicide of the year. Police continue to investigate his killing.",
        "_id": "22",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
