    "origin_url": "http://ottawacitizen.wpdev5.canada.com/business/energy/expect-one-more-day-of-hot-humid-weather-in-ottawa-before-temperatures-cool/wcm/97a78f62-e7bb-4b42-9e04-9b1fcc95743e",
    "status": "published",
    "titles": {
      "main": "Expect one more day of hot, humid weather in Ottawa before temperatures cool"
    },
    "content_elements": [
      {
        "content": "Brace yourself for one more day of blasting heat and humidity before temperatures drop to more seasonable, reasonable levels on Tuesday.",
        "_id": "1",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Monday is expected to reach 29 C, with a chance of thundershowers in the afternoon.",
        "_id": "2",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "But Tuesday, Environment Canada is calling for a high of 24 C, with no humidity, a welcome break from a three-day heat wave of temperatures above 30 C. Sunday&acirc;s blistering 33.2 C set a record, beating the high of 31.7 set in 1978. Saturday&acirc;s high was 32.2 C, and both days featured high humidity.",
        "_id": "3",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Temperatures will start to climb by mid-week, though, and there will be a return of the dreaded humidex. Wednesday&acirc;s forecast is a high of 25, while Thursday will be 26 with a humidex of 29, according to the Weather Network.",
        "_id": "4",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "The hot, humid weather on the weekend forced organizers of Ottawa Race Weekend to adjust race times to help runners avoid the most intense heat. Saturday&acirc;s 10K race was moved back&Acirc;&nbsp;by half an hour, while half-marathoners on Sunday morning began 45 minutes early. And the marathon was cut short for &Acirc;&nbsp;late-finishing runners. Shortly after 11 a.m., at around the four-hour mark of the race, officials closed a 10-kilometre stretch of the course. They feared for the safety of slower runners who might be on the course for another hour and 15 minutes, when &Acirc;&nbsp;humidex readings might be as high as 40 C.",
        "_id": "5",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      }
    ],
