    "origin_url": "http://ottawacitizen.wpdev5.canada.com/entertainment/local-arts/meat-loaf-every-time-i-sing-bat-out-of-hell-its-like-the-first-time-ive-ever-done-it/wcm/96788345-9ee8-445e-9784-6dd982a23eb8",
    "status": "published",
    "titles": {
      "main": "Meat Loaf: \"Every time I sing Bat Out of Hell, it's like the first time I've ever done it.\""
    },
    "content_elements": [
      {
        "content": "Meat Loaf doesn&acirc;t do much sightseeing when he&acirc;s on the road. The 68-year-old rock legend, who is actually known as Meat to the people around him, prefers to&Acirc;&nbsp;focus on preserving his voice and getting enough sleep.",
        "_id": "1",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "&acirc;On the road, the most important thing is the show,&acirc; said the former Marvin Lee Aday in a recent phone interview. &acirc;I&acirc;m very disciplined. When we have a day off, I don&acirc;t talk. I don&acirc;t go out. I don&acirc;t leave my room. I never go out for dinner or to movies. I don&acirc;t go to bars.&acirc;",
        "_id": "2",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "The larger-than-life singer/actor saves every ounce of energy for the stage, where he throws himself into character to tackle the octave-swooping grandiosity of the Jim Steinman-penned songs that made Meat Loaf a household name in the late 1970s.",
        "_id": "3",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "&acirc;Every time I sing Bat Out of Hell, it&acirc;s like the first time I&acirc;ve ever done it,&acirc; says the performer, explaining how he projects such passion every night. &acirc;If you come to a show and watch really closely, every song has different movements because they&acirc;re different characters. It&acirc;s like I run film in my head.&acirc;",
        "_id": "4",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Those tunes were unleashed to the world on the Todd Rundgren-produced 1977 opus, ",
        "_id": "5",
        "paragraph": "open",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "<em>Bat Out of Hell</em>",
        "_id": "6",
        "type": "raw_html",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": ", which has since become the fifth best-selling album of all time. Although Meat never stopped recording, performing or acting &acirc;&Acirc;&nbsp;in fact, he celebrates his 50th anniversary in showbiz next year &acirc;&Acirc;&nbsp;there&acirc;s no doubt that his career was defined by the ",
        "_id": "7",
        "paragraph": "none",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "<em>Bat</em>",
        "_id": "8",
        "type": "raw_html",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": " staples: The title track, along with&Acirc;&nbsp;Two of Of Three Ain&acirc;t Bad, You Took The Words Right Out of My Mouth, All Revved Up with No Place To Go, Heaven Can Wait and of course, Paradise by the Dashboard Light.",
        "_id": "9",
        "paragraph": "close",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "There were two follow-up ",
        "_id": "10",
        "paragraph": "open",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "<em>Bat</em>",
        "_id": "11",
        "type": "raw_html",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": " albums,&Acirc;&nbsp;1993&acirc;s ",
        "_id": "12",
        "paragraph": "none",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "<em>Bat Out of Hell II</em>",
        "_id": "13",
        "type": "raw_html",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": " and the 2006 project, ",
        "_id": "14",
        "paragraph": "none",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "<em>Bat out of Hell III: The Monster is Loose</em>",
        "_id": "15",
        "type": "raw_html",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": ", but no plans for a fourth. &acirc;From the time we did ",
        "_id": "16",
        "paragraph": "none",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "<em>Bat Out of Hell</em>",
        "_id": "17",
        "type": "raw_html",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": ", we said, &acirc;If this sells, we will do three.&acirc; And that&acirc;s what we did.&acirc;",
        "_id": "18",
        "paragraph": "close",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Still, it&acirc;s important to keep creating, and Meat Loaf does have a new project, his 13th studio effort, ready for a Sept. 16 release. ",
        "_id": "19",
        "paragraph": "open",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "<em>Braver Than We Are</em>",
        "_id": "20",
        "type": "raw_html",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": " is his first album in years based on material by Steinman, a sign that their occasionally rocky relationship has been smoothed out.",
        "_id": "21",
        "paragraph": "close",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "&acirc;We&acirc;ve always had a great relationship,&acirc; counters Meat. &acirc;The problem is when managers start to argue with each other, then they call lawyers, and then they tell me and Jim, &acirc;Don&acirc;t talk.&acirc; I said, &acirc;Screw this, I&acirc;m going around them&acirc; so I went straight to Jim and we&acirc;ve been in communication almost daily, sometimes for hours.&acirc;",
        "_id": "22",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "According to Meat, the album features reworked versions of lesser-known Steinman songs, including the first tune he ever wrote, Who Needs The Young. He describes the music as &acirc;completely different.",
        "_id": "23",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "&acirc;Every record we do is different,&acirc; he adds. &acirc;When ",
        "_id": "24",
        "paragraph": "open",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "<em>Bat</em>",
        "_id": "25",
        "type": "raw_html",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": " came out, it was so different than anything else. It took a while for people to even start to attempt to understand it. I&acirc;m keeping this one pretty much under wraps, but it&acirc;s very different, too.&acirc;",
        "_id": "26",
        "paragraph": "close",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "So much for the rumours of retirement, which appear to have started during his 2013 Last at Bat tour of Europe and the U.K. when Meat declared it would be his final tour. &acirc;People get this so wrong,&acirc; he says, keen to clarify. &acirc;I said that was going to be my last tour of Europe, but I still had a lot of shows to do. I knew I wasn&acirc;t retiring from touring as far as North America went, but I wasn&acirc;t planning on going back to Europe.&acirc;",
        "_id": "27",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "How come? &Acirc;&nbsp;&acirc;I&acirc;m almost 70 years old,&acirc; he notes. &acirc;Mick Jagger songs are a lot easier to sing than mine. I happen to love the Rolling Stones, but if I had to sing Mick Jagger songs, I could probably sing five nights a week. These songs, most of them cover three-and-a-half octaves. People have no idea how hard it is.&acirc;",
        "_id": "28",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "However, due to the overwhelming amount of requests from overseas fans, plans changed and Meat Loaf is planning to return to Europe and the United Kingdom one more time.",
        "_id": "29",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "In the meantime, Meat and his band are on a Canadian tour that includes out-of-the-way places like Cold Lake, Alta., and Moose Jaw, Sask. The singer says he&acirc;s been wanting to come back to Canada for years to make up for contracting pneumonia on one of his last tours.",
        "_id": "30",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "The original ",
        "_id": "31",
        "paragraph": "open",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "<em>Bat</em>",
        "_id": "32",
        "type": "raw_html",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": " tour was another ill-fated Canadian excursion. During a concert at the Ottawa Civic Centre on April 22, 1978, the 300-lb. Texan ventured a little too close to the edge of the stage and fell off. According to the ",
        "_id": "33",
        "paragraph": "none",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "<em>Citizen</em>",
        "_id": "34",
        "type": "raw_html",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": " review, the concert ended abruptly and Meat was reportedly taken to hospital by ambulance. He remembers the night.",
        "_id": "35",
        "paragraph": "close",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "&acirc;I got my foot caught in the cables,&acirc; he recalled. &acirc;I was hanging upside down. I was doing All Revved Up and I finished the song hanging upside down. It tore my knee to pieces, and so I wound up having some kind of operation on it. I didn&acirc;t miss very many shows. We did shows in a wheelchair, and then a walking cast.",
        "_id": "36",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "While he learned&Acirc;&nbsp;a lesson about watching where he steps, his full-tilt approach to performing hasn&acirc;t changed much.",
        "_id": "37",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "&acirc;Every show is so important to me,&acirc; Meat says. &acirc;I don&acirc;t walk through anything. I get to the show five hours before and nobody comes into my dressing room 30 minutes before the show. I&acirc;m a different human being. I go to the zone. Me and the band, we will hit you hard. My objective is to leave when the audience leaves, and to make sure they feel tired.&acirc;",
        "_id": "38",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      }
    ],
