    "origin_url": "http://ottawacitizen.wpdev5.canada.com/entertainment/local-arts/test-post/wcm/9f7b5786-860a-4142-bcaa-4179a0b9d9c6",
    "status": "published",
    "titles": {
      "main": "Update: Heat wave hunkers down over Ottawa area (again)"
    },
    "content_elements": [
      {
        "content": "Brace yourself, another heat wave has hit the Ottawa Valley.",
        "_id": "1",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Environment Canada issued a reminder warning early Wednesday that the latest hot and humid air mass is expected to smother Ottawa and area until at least Friday, with only moderate relief in sight.",
        "_id": "2",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Daytime highs are&Acirc;&nbsp;expected to stay between 31 C and 34 C, complicated by humidex readings that could make it feel like 40 at times.",
        "_id": "3",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Gatineau has stepped up to offer some relief, extending the opening hours at city beaches and wading/splash pools by an hour today.",
        "_id": "4",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Wednesday morning readings showed good water conditions at the ",
        "_id": "5",
        "paragraph": "open",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "<a href=\"http://ottawa.ca/en/residents/parks-and-recreation/parks-and-sports-fields/daily-water-quality-results\">City of Ottawaâs five official beaches</a>",
        "_id": "6",
        "type": "raw_html",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": ".",
        "_id": "7",
        "paragraph": "close",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "<div id=\"fsk_splitbox_1715\" class=\"  fsk_splitbox_1715     sb-opened\"></div>",
        "_id": "8",
        "type": "raw_html",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Ottawa paramedics reported two cases of children left in locked cars on Tuesday.",
        "_id": "9",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Environment Canada said this might be &acirc;the longest and most significant heat wave of the summer so far.&acirc;",
        "_id": "10",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Ottawans won&acirc;t get much relief overnight, either, with lows expected to be in the 20s into Friday.",
        "_id": "11",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Showers and thunderstorms may move through the Valley sometime Friday, with a 40-per-cent chance of rain forecast. Environment Canada said if the rain comes, Ottawa could see a&Acirc;&nbsp;reprieve from the heat just in time for the weekend.",
        "_id": "12",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "It reminded residents to frequently visit neighbours, friends and the elderly &acirc; especially those who are ill &acirc; to make sure they&acirc;re keeping cool and hydrated since there&acirc;s an increased risk of heat-related illnesses such as heat exhaustion and heat stroke when a heat warning is in effect.",
        "_id": "13",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "Environment Canada advised that outdoor activities be planned or rescheduled for cooler parts of the day to avoid heat-related illnesses and also stressed that you should never&Acirc;&nbsp;leave people or pets inside a parked vehicle or in direct sunlight when temperatures are high.",
        "_id": "14",
        "paragraph": "wrap",
        "type": "text",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "content": "<hr>\n",
        "_id": "15",
        "type": "raw_html",
        "channels": [
          "desktop",
          "tablet",
          "phone"
        ]
      },
      {
