        "content": "<div> <p>Police in Gatineau have launched an investigation after two men, one in a clown mask the other in a clown âsuitâ and facepaint, wandered through a city park MondayÂ afternoon scaring a number of children.</p> <p>According to reports received by police, at least two children were scared by the men, one of whom was dragging a chain, at Limbour Park in the Farmers Rapids neighbourhood of old Gatineau.</p> <p>None of the children were touched or injured by the men.</p> <p>One of the clowns, wearing a red T-shirt and jeans, clown calmly posed for pictures by a concernedÂ mother before wandering off.</p> <p>Facebook postings on the incidents garnered dozens of comments from concerned parents.</p> <div id=\"fsk_splitbox_1715\" class=\"  fsk_splitbox_1715\"></div> <p>Police in Gatineau confirmed Wednesday morning that they are investigating the incident.</p> <figure class=\"wp-caption post-img size_this_image_test aligncenter\" id=\"attachment_860563\"><img class=\"wp-image-860563 size-full\" src=\"http://wpmedia.ottawacitizen.com/2016/08/facebook-photo-of-a-clown-who-showed-up-at-a-gatineau-area-p-e1470836436739.jpeg?quality=55&amp;strip=all\" alt=\"Facebook photo of a clown who showed up at a Gatineau area park and scared some children.\"><figcaption class=\"wp-caption-text wp-caption\"><span class=\"img-caption\"> Facebook photo of a clown dragging a chain in a Gatineau park. In the distance, a second suspect can be seen dressed in a baggy clown costume.</span> </figcaption></figure><p> </p> </div>",
